title: roman apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Beat in shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in apples by hand.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan (for deeper cake), then cover batter with topping.

title: miss lou's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Gently stir in vanilla. Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Yields 5 dozen.

title: fruitcake grice style
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Blend.
Add flour and salt. Fold in fruit mix and nuts.
Put into 3 greased and floured 1-pound loaf pans or in a fruitcake pan.
Start in cold oven; bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: waffle batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
(Don't overmix, okay to be lumpy.)
Preheat waffle iron.
Lightly brush waffle iron with oil before pouring batter.
Cook until very lightly browned or darker if desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil, then add eggs, pumpkin and spices.
Then add flour and water and then raisins.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: stuffed sausage links
directions: Split sausage links lengthwise, making a pocket.
Place in a baking pan.
Prepare potatoes according to package, omitting the salt and decrease liquid by 2 tablespoons.
Stir in onion.
Spoon mixture into sausage pockets.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: yum chicken
directions: Wrap a slice of bacon around each piece of chicken; secure with toothpicks.
Place on greased 10 x 7-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 2 hours.

title: oven baked chicken with fruit
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil.
Drain.
Arrange pieces in an oblong baking dish.
Combine pineapple and barbecue sauce; spread over chicken.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 3 to 24 hours. Bake, covered, at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Spoon off fat. Garnish with oranges; spoon sauce over all.
Serve with rice.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Mix
water,
vinegar and sugar together; heat until all ingredients
are dissolved.
Set aside.
Fry bacon;
drain and leave only enough drippings in skillet to fry the cabbage; fry for about 5 to 10 minutes, until tender and slightly browned. Add salt, pepper, water, vinegar and sugar mixture.
Sprinkle crushed red pepper on top and simmer 5 more minutes.
Top with crisp bacon.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Trim the ends of the eggplants, but do not peel. Cut each eggplant crosswise into 9 slices, each approximately 1/2-inch thick.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a double boiler or microwave. Mix by hand the remaining evaporated milk, pecans, margarine and cake mix. Mixture will be very thick. Pat half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Remove from oven. Pour chocolate chips over. Then spread on caramel mixture. Crumble remaining cake mixture on top of caramel mixture. Bake 18 to 20 minutes. Let set and cool before cutting. Freezes well. Yield: 2 to 3 dozen.

title: soursop tizan
directions: Peel soursop and place in large bowl.
Crush with potato masher or use hands to separate.
Pour hot water over pulp.
Cover and let stand 1/2 hour.
In colander, strain off juice, agitating the pulp with a spoon.
To soursop juice, add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Using blender (electric), add 1 cup soursop mixture and whirl a few seconds.
Continue doing so until all liquid has been well blended.
Makes 1/2 gallon soursop tizan.
Can be poured into ice cube trays and frozen like ice cream.

title: chocolate yum yum's
directions: Grate chocolate.
Add water, sugar and syrup.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add peanuts and flavoring.
Cool slightly.
Beat until mixture begins to crystalize.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: brown sugar glaze for ham
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon over ham several times during last 30 minutes of baking.
Garnish with pecans 10 minutes before ham is done.

title: okra dill pickle
directions: Use small tender pods of okra, cut with as much stem as possible.
Wash and drain.
Prick each pod with pin or fine pointed knife to allow solution to enter pod.
Pack okra into jars.
Place a small bunch of dill in each jar with okra.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add alternately with milk to butter mixture. Stir just to blend; fold in berries.
Spoon batter into 12 greased muffin tins.
Sprinkle each with granulated sugar (optional). Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: crazy cabbage
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add cabbage and cans tomatoes. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes to desired consistency.

title: mushroom croustades
directions: *I use the Cuisinart.

title: pineapple-orange salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well with a spoon or spatula.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Melt oleo and mix flour and sugar.
Mold in pie pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry lime cake
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the marshmallows in the bottom of the pan.
Mix cake mix according to instructions on box and pour over marshmallows.
Mix strawberries, dry strawberry jello mix, dry lime jello mix and sugar together and spoon over cake batter.
Bake according to instructions on cake mix box.

title: crock-pot cubed beef
directions: Place cubed beef in crock-pot.
Cover with soups and water and mix in bouillon.
Place cubed potatoes on top.
Turn crock-pot on low.

title: oyster casserole
directions: In 3-quart casserole, use half of oysters.
Add 1/2 cup celery and 1/2 of Ritz cracker crumbs.
Then add other oysters, celery and cracker crumbs.
Pour half and half cream and butter, melted, on top of casserole.
Bake in oven at 325° until lightly brown. Serves 10 or more.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook beef, sausage and onion. Brown and drain off excess fat. Add soup, cheese and salsa; mix well.
Put in crock-pot to keep warm.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and blend together well.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until bubbling.
Remove from heat and stir in evaporated milk and chicken broth.
Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Stir in chicken, heat and serve.
Do not let boil or it will be grainy.
Serve over hot biscuits, noodles or your preference.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry corn-bran muffins(12 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line 12 muffin cups or spray with Pam. In large mixing bowl or food processor, combine bran, cornmeal, sugar and baking powder.
In small mixing bowl, combine milk and oil; stir into the dry ingredients and stir in the blueberries. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold them into the batter.
Spoon batter into muffin cups and bake 20 minutes.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Chop chipped ham up into little pieces in a bowl.
Add chopped onions, celery, eggs and cheese.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vinegar and red food coloring.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Pour into cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(One cup of nuts can be added to batter, if you wish.)

title: roasted garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Place garlic on a square of aluminum foil and drizzle with oil. Wrap tightly. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and set aside. This can be done ahead.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Place round steak in crock-pot.
Push meat up sides.
Add vegetables.
Dissolve beef cubes in water.
Add sugar, tapioca and salt.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cook 8 hours on low in crock-pot.
Add Kitchen Bouquet for color, if desired.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
Add to cake mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add morsels and nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: marinated sausage
directions: Mix barbecue sauce, brown sugar, catsup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Steam sausage 15 or 20 minutes and pour off liquid.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add sausage.
Cut to desired size.
Marinate overnight.
Ready to heat and serve the next day.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Place 1 piece of white bread on top of mixture and bake, covered, at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Once during baking time, stir bread down into stew as a thickener.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Beat sugar, salt and eggs together.
Add milk and cornstarch (moisten the cornstarch with a little milk).
Add corn and melted butter.
Stir together well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Set in pan of hot water, as a custard, about 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: tomato soup
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil and simmer 2 hours. Strain. Blend the remaining ingredients. Add this blended mixture to the tomato mixture slowly.
Bring to a boil. Sprinkle with cloves when serving.
This is a good way to use surplus tomatoes in the fall.

title: philadelphia cream cheese spread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook until thick.
Add cream cheese.
Grind peppers and onion and mix altogether.

title: squash bread
directions: Beat eggs until thick. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well after adding each one. Place into well-greased and floured bread pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Dice the potatoes and cook with onion.
Drain and put into a greased casserole dish. Melt the oleo; dice the bread and put into oleo.
Add the oleo mixture to potatoes and mix.
Cover with corn flakes.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked stuffed clams
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in shells and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Arrange banana slices on bottom of crust.
Set aside.

title: mom's real homemade spaghetti
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, crackers, onion and beef.
Roll into small meatballs.
Fry in skillet until done.
In skillet, combine oil, water and chopped onion.
Brown lightly.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spread graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 10x sugar, eggs, vanilla and soft margarine.
Beat until fluffy and spread in pan.
Place pineapple on top of filling.
Cut bananas lengthwise and place on top of pineapple, then spread Cool Whip over top.
Finish with peanuts and maraschino cherries.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 13 minutes. Remove from oven and press Hershey Kiss on top.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Use all flour on fruit.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and add flavorings.
Combine with fruit and nuts.
Bake at 300° until done.
It makes about 5 pound cake.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Using shredding disc, shred potatoes.
Transfer to medium bowl and add cold water to cover.
Using steel blade, process onion, using on/off technique, until finely chopped.
Add eggs, flour, butter, salt and pepper to bowl.
Drain potatoes; pat dry with paper toweling and add to bowl.
Process just until mixture is blended.
Heat 1/4-inch oil in skillet.
Spoon about 1/4 cup potato mixture into skillet for each pancake; flatten with spatula.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Drain pancakes on paper toweling and serve immediately.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Heat and pour over jello.
Cool and add Coke.
Chill until thick.
Stir in grated cream cheese, cherries, pineapple and pecans.

title: sunday supper casserole
directions: Melt vegetable oil, add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened and beginning to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mustard and cheese.
Cut or dice ham.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, ham and cheese sauce in 2-quart casserole which has been rubbed with Crisco or sprayed with vegetable oil.
Top with cheese sauce.
Bake in slow oven, 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry salad mold
directions: Drain juice
from berries, reserve.
Add juice to jello dissolved in the
boiling
water.
Pour
half
of mixture into large mold or 9
x	13-inch
pan.
Let it set.
Let other half get syrupy, to it add the blueberries and prepared Dream Whip. Pour on top
of
jello
in	mold.
Chill
several hours before unmolding.

title: delicious shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup to a boil. Add softened gelatin that has been mixed with water. Add softened cream cheese and blend well.
Cool and add other ingredients. Chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: beatrice griffin's dutch lettuce
directions: Cut lettuce.
Add onions.
Add sugar, salt, vinegar and pepper to hot drippings quickly, all at once.
Pour over lettuce and onions.
Serve at once.

title: raisin honey chews
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, honey, egg and peel.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and oats.
Beat well.
Add raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until evenly browned.
Let stand on sheet 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well.
Pour into pie shells. Prepared graham cracker or cookie crusts may be used.
Can be frozen.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat oleo, sugars, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl vigorously until creamy and well blended. Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix with a spoon until too stiff and then use hands.
Yield: 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Combine clam chowder and minced clams.
Add cooked potatoes and hard boiled eggs and milk.
Heat through and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk together in
a bowl.
Fold in fruit and Cool Whip; let set in refrigerator until gels.
Other fruit can be added if desired.

title: sunshine orange mousse pie
directions: In blender, sprinkle gelatine over cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Add hot cream and process at low speed until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add cream cheese, juice concentrate, sugar and vanilla; process until blended.
Chill until mixture is slightly thickened, about 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown beef with onion. Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
Recipe may be cut in half.

title: carrot-raisin relish
directions: Mix carrots and raisins in bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar; toss lightly.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Combine mayonnaise, cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Stir into carrot mixture just before serving.
Spoon into lettuce cups.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's old fashioned potato soup
directions: Pour 2 quarts water in a large pot.
Peel potatoes and cut up in small pieces.
Cook until potatoes smash up easy with fork. Put salt, pepper and margarine and let boil up real good about 3 minutes.
Mix flour in cup with 1/3 cup water.
Add cream to flour.
Pour flour mix in with potatoes.
Stir very good.
Let boil; stir.
When comes to full boil set off stove.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jacket until tender, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain water and let cool.
Peel potatoes and grate potatoes as hash brown potatoes.
Mix in onion, cheese, soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with stuffing and pour melted butter over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove cover last 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts and dates last.
Drop by teaspoons onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: creamy pear jello
directions: Drain pears (save juice).
Heat 1 cup of pear juice.
Dissolve jello with pear juice.
Puree pears in blender.
Add cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Add jello mixture and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: hawaiian chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add all ingredients, except the rice.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook rice according to package.
Serve chili over rice.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix well the flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla pudding, butter, egg and milk and pour into a pie dish.
Place peaches over batter.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Spread on top of peaches.
Leave 1-inch from the edge.
Sprinkle with sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, syrup, nuts, salt, vanilla and chipped butter.
Put into pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown
chicken	pieces	in
tablespoons
olive
oil. Remove to
platter.
Saute onion and garlic in same olive oil (do
not burn
garlic).
Add bell pepper;
continue to saute. Add
olive oil
by
the tablespoonful, if needed.
Add tomato paste;
blend with sauteed veggies.
Add crushed tomatoes, 1/2 cup
water, chicken, herbs and mushrooms; cook on low heat for 30
minutes. Add
red wine; cook 25 more minutes.
Serve over pasta or rice. Bon appetit!

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press evenly into pan.
Arrange the banana slices on the crust.
Beat the cream cheese in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat until well blended. Spread evenly over banana slices.
Spoon pineapple evenly over pudding mixture.
Put whipped topping over the pineapple.
Enjoy.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Put the sliced apples in the pie crust.
Cook together the apple juice, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice; bring to a boil to thicken.
Pour over apples.
Put on top of crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until brown and apples are done.

title: mint puffs
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to form a semi-firm ball.
Pour egg white, heating constantly until mixture holds firm.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add 2 to 3 drops of coloring and 1 drop of flavoring.
Beat until smooth and blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper, swirling top of each puff.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cream cheese and olive spread
directions: Put cream cheese in food processor and process for 30 to 40 seconds.
Add whole green olives, 2 at a time, and process.
Taste and add olives as needed to reach desired taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; season with salt and pepper.
Drain meat and onion.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan, pour milk 1/4-inch deep.
Put down a layer of tortillas, then a layer of meat, 1/2 of soup and cheese.
Pour 1/2 of remaining milk and repeat layers again.
Top with cheese and chiles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Drain juices from oranges and pineapple.
Mix everything together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: sara's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients together, beat thoroughly.
Grease tube pan; pour in cake batter and bake for approximately 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Beat until thick, then fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch
dish, layer the bottom with graham crackers (whole, not crushed).
Put a layer of mix, then another layer of crackers and mix, ending with a layer of crackers on top.

title: strawberry and cream cake
directions: Rinse, cap and slice strawberries. Pinch cake into small pieces; set aside. Mix berries and glaze; set aside.
Combine Cool Whip, sour cream, yogurt, milk and sugar. In large bowl, layer cake, whipped topping mixture and strawberries. Repeat layers. Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: tuna crescent melt
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Then add tuna and eggs.
Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles.
Place on sprayed cookie sheet, overlapping long sides at center 1/2-inch. Press edges and perforations to seal.
Spoon tuna mixture down center into a strip and top with cheese.
Make cuts or slits on sides of dough.
Bring over tuna mixture for a braided look.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes or golden brown.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Put remaining ingredients in 5-quart saucepan.
Add 1 quart of water.
Bring to boil at high heat.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook about 45 minutes or until potatoes are done, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peperonata with potatoes
directions: Cut peppers lengthwise.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Potatoes are diced.
Coarsely chop tomatoes.
Place olive oil and margarine in braising pan.
Heat on medium flame and when butter melts, cook onion until it softens and becomes light golden.
Add peppers, potatoes, tomatoes, 4 basil leaves, salt and pepper.
Stir the mixture; cover and cook over low heat for about 40 minutes.
Be careful not to overcook potatoes.
Before serving, coarsely chop remaining basil.
Transfer stew to serving dish and sprinkle with chopped basil.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add seasoning and Chili-O mix.
Then add tomatoes and beans.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Pour into casserole dish and top with Fritos and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and add dry ingredients, then liquids.
Bake in shallow pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes or in loaf pan in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in a 2-quart saucepan.
Blend with a wooden spoon and place over low heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Put in a candy thermometer and boil without stirring over medium heat until thermometer registers 256°. Remove from heat and let stand while 2 egg whites are beaten stiff; add a dash of salt.
Slowly add syrup to egg whites, beating until candy holds a definite shape and loses its gloss. One teaspoon vanilla is stirred in just before candy is dropped by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Walnuts or pecans can be added.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix ingredients togther. Bake at 400 for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cukes and slice as thin as possible.
Chop onions and peppers and combine with the cukes and the salt.
Let stand 3 hours and drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Add drained cukes and heat thoroughly but do not bring to a boil.
Pack while hot into sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: rhonda's chicken
directions: Preheat
oven to 375°.	Put rice in casserole; add soup and water.
Season
the
chicken with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Put
chicken
on
top of rice.
Place casserole in oven for
1 hour.
Turn chicken 30 minutes in the cooking process. Check to make sure rice is not drying out, if so, add water.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: broccoli and zucchini pasta
directions: Steam broccoli in a small amount of water or in a steamer basket until crisp-tender, about 7 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti.
Make a sauce by stir-frying garlic and zucchini in oil until zucchini is barely tender.
Add oregano and salt and pepper. Melt butter into sauce, then add broccoli.
Toss sauce with spaghetti and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ruby's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Put flour in a large bowl.
Make a hole in flour.
Pour buttermilk, yeast, sugar and oil in flour. Stir with a spoon to make dough.
Knead on board.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Fold over with melted butter and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 450° until brown. Melt butter and pour just a little bit on each roll before putting in oven to bake.
When making dough the night before, it will keep in the refrigerator 4 to 5 days.

title: strawberry jello pineapple pie
directions: Bring to a boil the Jell-O, pineapple and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to cold (not stiff).
Whip evaporated milk (I use Pet milk) which has been chilled in fridge.
Fold in Jell-O mixture.
Place on cold, baked pie shell or graham cracker crust. Swirl top.
Makes 1 large or 2 small pies.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Heat oil or fat in large skillet.
Add finely chopped garlic, green pepper and onion.
Cook without browning 5 minutes.
Add ground beef; mix well and cook on high heat until lightly brown. Add tomato paste, tomato puree and boiling water.
Simmer 1 hour or longer (if desired).
Add seasonings last 15 minutes of cooking.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the eggs, brown sugar, white sugar, milk, vanilla and Wesson oil.
Add the dry ingredients.
Form into balls; dip in sugar.
Press a little flat with hand.
Bake at 350°.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Makes 24 (1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup and sour cream and add chili powder and garlic powder; set aside.
Dice cooked chicken; add sauteed onion and grated cheese.
Mix.
Soften tortillas in hot chicken broth.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Cut grapefruit sections into halves.
Mix grapefruit, oranges, grapes and corn syrup.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours but not longer than 24 hours.
Stir in banana and coconut just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, melted margarine and flour.
Add pineapple. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients except for corn flakes/chips.
Pour in a grease a 9 x 13 inch cake pan.
Cover with corn flakes/chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: If using regular-size hot dogs, slice into 1-inch pieces. Blend remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add hot dogs and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: orange-tarragon butter
directions: In a bowl of food processor fitted with a metal wing blade, place butter, tarragon, orange peel, salt and black pepper; process using on and off motions until combined, about 30 seconds. (Or place all ingredients in a medium bowl; stir until combined.) Serve with hot cooked corn-on-the-cob or other steamed vegetables.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar. Bring to boil (do not boil) the Coke, margarine, Crisco and cocoa. Pour chocolate mixture over dry mixture. Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
Mix Bisquick and margarine until crumbly.

Add the skim milk slowly and stir until dough forms a ball (about 15 strokes). Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart on the cookie sheet. Make a well in the middle of each with the back of a spoon and add 1 teaspoon of All Fruit type jelly.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Contains 7 fat and 140 calories.
Serves 12.

title: beef-tater tots casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion.
Add Tater Tots, corn, peas and pimento.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover with grated cheese. Pour undiluted soup over all.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower in mixing bowl.
Add peas, chopped celery and sliced carrots.
Add cottage cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine, sugar and salt; add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring by hand.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Do not open door while baking.
Remove from pan immediately.
Set oven temperature at 325°.
Do not preheat oven.
Start in cold oven.

title: chicken thighs and rice
directions: In a 10-inch skillet cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Brown chicken in reserve drippings, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Cook rice, onion wedges and garlic in skillet drippings until rice is golden brown.
Stir frequently.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms, wine, bouillon granules, salt, basil and 1 cup water.

title: champagne rose punch
directions: In large bowl combine strawberries and 3 1/4 cups (4/5 quart) Rose wine.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Strain mixture into punch bowl or puree mixture in blender.
Add thawed lemonade, remaining Rose wine, champagne and ice to keep punch chilled.
Mix well and serve.
Makes approximately 27 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Mix ingredients and put on greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spicy wok chicken
directions: Pour enough cooking oil to cover bottom of wok.
Cut up chicken into small pieces.
Cut up onions and bell peppers thinly. Fry chicken in cooking oil with minced onions, garlic and Tony Chachere.
Pour in Worcestershire.
Add cut up bell peppers and onions.
Bring to a boil; continuously mix.
Reduce heat to low and cover for 15 minutes.
Pour over rice or pasta.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over the melted butter.
Drain cherries and save liquid.
Arrange cherries over the batter.
Combine the 1/2 cup sugar with cherry juice and pour over the cherries.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender for 30 seconds at low speed. Pour into ungreased 10-inch pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers, apples, onions and carrots in food grinder. Pour 1 pint boiling water into which is dissolved the 2 tablespoons of salt over the ground vegetables.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar, red peppers and 2 teaspoons salt.
Add vegetables and cook for 20 minutes.
Pack into jars and water bath process.

title: lemon delight
directions: Combine and beat 3 minutes.
Spread over chilled layer. Spread Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: banana marshmallow dessert
directions: Place banana and marshmallows in covered bowl; set aside. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Combine water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until jello begins to thicken.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Pour over the banana and marshmallows. Refrigerate until set.
Keep covered.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 1 or 2 crust pie shells at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in milk, then in crumbs mixed with rosemary and pepper.
Place in shallow pan coated with Pam or foil.
Let stand briefly.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together the first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheets and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 11 to 12 cups.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 inch tube pan.
Peel and slice apples, mix with sugar and cinnamon to coat well.
In separate bowl beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add oil and beat.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix with orange juice and vanilla.
Pour 1/4 batter into pan.
Arrange 1/3 apples over batter.
Continue pattern, ending with batter. Bake at 350 degrees for 90 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil while stirring. Great over chicken, ribs or chops.

title: chicken and "trees" casserole
directions: Put chicken meat, broccoli and peas in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine sauce ingredients and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
Good served over rice.

title: boiled custard
directions: Cook in double boiler or extra heavy saucepan, stirring constantly with whip or wooden spoon until this mixture thickens or coats a silver spoon.
Add vanilla and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well. Put into a greased and floured jelly roll pan or deep cookie sheet. Sprinkle with nuts and coconut as desired. Bake roll in 350° oven until firm, 10 to 15 minutes. Loosen roll and place on towel covered with 10x sugar. Cover with sugar and roll up; set aside to cool.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise or dressing.
Arrange on crisp lettuce leaves.
Serve at once because apples turn dark quickly.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain and cut mandarin oranges.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in shallow, 3-quart baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Combine in given order.
Pinch off small portions and press flat with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef and potato pie
directions: Prepare pie crust mix according to package directions; roll out for 2 crust (10-inch) pie.
Line pie plate with pastry. Combine meat and soups.
Lightly pat into pastry-lined plate.
Top with potatoes.
Place slices of cheese on top.
Add crust; seal. Flute edge.
Cut design in top pastry.
Bake at 350° oven for about 1 hour or until browned.
Serve with warm catsup, if desired.
tags: loose pack frozen hash brown potatoes

title: fried rice
directions: Place the eggs, scallions, ginger, garlic, rice, salt, sugar, soy sauce, ham and peas in small containers or on paper plates near the cooking area.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour over roast. Cover and bake 6 hours at 350°. After cooked, shred meat with 2 forks. Serve with hard rolls. Also good over rice.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 275° for 15 minutes.
Great for a snack.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and nutmeg. Pour in pie shell and cook for 45 minutes at 350 degrees. the unbaked pie crust may be put in hot oven and baked 3 to 5 minutes to help prevent a soggy crust.

title: elvis presley's favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with cream.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for
1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: 50's style pizza
directions: Measure dry ingredients into bowl.
Stir mustard into milk; blend milk and shortening into dry ingredients.
Roll or press into 9 x 13 cake pan.
Prick surface with fork.
Bake in hot oven, 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove.
Reduce heat to 375°.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by tablespoons. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine
chicken,
celery,
grapes
and
almonds.
Toss mixture lightly with
sour	cream and mayonnaise.
(If mixture seems a little dry, add a
tiny bit of honey.) Serve on a half or quartered cantaloupe.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jessie's stir-fry
directions: Coat in meal with a little flour added.
Cook in oil on medium to high heat.
Stir regular.
Do not overcook.
May also add hot pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In a greased 2 1/2 quart casserole dish, mix beans, corn, salt and pepper.
Add already mixed together celery soup, cheese, onions and sour cream to beans and corn.
Add cracker and almonds on top. Slice butter real thin and place on top of almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Note:
Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine strawberries
and
sugar;
let
stand
2 hours. Drain off juice and add
water to it to make 2 cups of liquid. Blend in cornstarch
and
cook
over low heat until thickened. Mix with strawberries;
cool.
Put
into
baked
pie
crust or graham cracker crust pie shell and serve with whipped cream.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk; set aside.
Grease muffin pan. Mix together dry
ingredients.
Cut in shortening until coarse crumbs form.
Stir
eggs
into
cereal
mixture and add to dry ingredients until moistened.
Pour
into muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: orange refrigerator salad
directions: Sprinkle dry gelatin over cottage cheese.
Drain oranges and pineapple and add them to cottage cheese mixture.
Stir gently to mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
In skillet, melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, all at once.
Stir until thick and bubbly.
Pour over cooked macaroni.
Stir in cheese and mix together well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add slices of butter on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
This dish is even better when reheated and served the next day.
I usually separate the macaroni with a fork slightly; add a little more butter and microwave until warm.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix together and bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add marshmallows, cherries, cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise and mix up.
Whip the cream; fold into other mixture.
Chill and serve.
Nuts may be added on top of mixture.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, bread crumbs and ketchup together.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Take out of oven and pour off the grease. Mix together ketchup, water, mustard and brown sugar; pour over the meat loaf.
Cook 35 minutes longer.

title: wine chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Put in large skillet with butter.
Saute until chicken is no longer pink.
Drain green beans and mushrooms.
Add to chicken in skillet.
Add port wine.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: peach apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly grease 9 x 9 x 2 inch casserole dish.
Combine peaches, apples, vanilla and cinnamon in a bowl.
Toss well and spread evenly in greased casserole dish. Combine flour and sugar in small bowl.
Cut in margarine with knife until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle flour mixture evenly over fruit.
Bake until lightly browned and bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot fat.
Add water, tomato sauce, thinly sliced onion and minced garlic.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and cook about 1 hour or until tender.
Skim most of fat from gravy.
Dilute with water to suit taste; then thicken with 2 tablespoons of flour mixed to a smooth paste with a little water.

title: burrito roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients, except tortillas.
Spread 1 1/2 tablespoons on entire tortilla.
Roll tightly and wrap in wax paper.
Chill 8 hours.
Slice into 1-inch pieces and serve with picante sauce.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire and garlic salt.
Mix, then stir in shrimp with fork.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Mix in blender the first 6 ingredients, then place in saucepan.
Add cheese and milk as needed. Stir over heat until cheese melts.

title: grandma jane's cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 9 x 13-inch pan.
After removing from oven, poke holes in cake.
Pour condensed milk over top and cool.
Put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut. Place plastic wrap on top and refrigerate.
Simple but really good!

title: country cornbread stuffing
directions: In a small skillet, saute celery and onion until tender. Combine celery mixture, cornbread, bread cubes, sausage and sage. Mix well.
Add broth, water and eggs.
Toss until moist.
Add more water if more moist dressing is desired.
Makes enough stuffing for a 12 to 16 pound turkey.
Bake remaining stuffing 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir cake mix and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan or two 9-inch round pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes clean.
Cool and frost as desired.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: grilled sirloin steak
directions: Brush grill with oil.
Place steak on grill as close as possible to heat.
Sear for 2 minutes on one side only.
Raise grill approximately 4 inches above heat source and continue grilling until tiny bubbles appear on top of steak.
Only then turn the steak with tongs.
Do not use fork or any utensil that will pierce the meat.
Turn only once!
Repeat above for second side.
When done, brush with butter on each side.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cut against the grain.

title: morning pumpkin coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 10-inch tube or Bundt pan with no stick cooking spray.
Beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Mix in pumpkin, egg white and water.
Gradually add combined flour, 1 1/4 cups oats and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread into pan; sprinkle with 1/4 cup oats.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by teaspoons on foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Leave space for mixture to spread.
Let cool and peel foil from bottom of cookies.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into strips about 2 1/2-inch long 1/2-inch thick. Slice onions and mushrooms finely.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in frying pan, cook onions slowly until golden brown, remove from pan, keep warm.
Add a little more butter, cook mushrooms about 5 minutes, add to onions.
Melt remaining butter.
When foaming, put in about 1/2 the strips of steak, fry quickly about 5 minutes until brown on both sides, remove.
Repeat with remaining steak. Replace all meat and vegetables in pan, shake over heat adding salt and pepper and nutmeg, add sour cream.
Heat until it nearly boils.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: deluxe sugar cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Divide dough in half and roll out 3/16-inch thick on lightly floured board covered with a cloth.
Cut into shapes, sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: christmas jello salad(sugar-free)
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Pour into square glass dish.
Chill until partly set.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add Equal, drained pineapple juice and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended and stir in crushed pineapple.
Cool slightly.
Fold in mayonnaise and yogurt and chill until almost set.
Pour over lime jello already in dish. Chill.
Dissolve cherry jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water and chill until syrupy.
Pour over pineapple and cream cheese layer.
Chill until firm.

title: better than bruce's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving 1/4 can tomato sauce.
Put into skillet; cover with remaining tomato sauce.
Cook in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter, oil, caramels and marshmallows in microwave on High until melted, 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour over popcorn, M&M's, Reese's Pieces and peanuts.
Pack into lightly oiled angel food or Bundt cake pan.
Refrigerate to set.

title: candy
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into buttered pan.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.

title: grandmother ray's chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; cook over medium heat until very thick.
Add the butter and vanilla.
Let set 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: bake beans
directions: Saute celery, pepper and onion in margarine.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and top with bacon strips.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Pour milk over oats; let stand.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir eggs into oats-milk mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in oil.
Bake on hot, lightly greased griddle or frypan until golden brown, turning only once.
(For variety, sprinkle on pancakes before turning:
chopped apples, finely chopped luncheon meat, cooked corn, cooked sausage, or chopped cooked ham.)
Serve pancakes hot with syrup.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups of hot water.
Let cool.
Add drained pineapple, chopped bananas and marshmallows and nuts.
Let gel.
Combine sugar, juice from pineapple, flour and egg and cook until thick.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold in cooked mixture; spread on Jell-O and cover with grated cheese.

title: mud slide cake
directions: Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
After mixing, press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Mix 1/2 Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread on cooled, baked mixture. Combine chocolate and vanilla puddings and milk; spread on top. Spread on other 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Grate Hershey bar on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: unfried chicken
directions: In shallow dish, mix together first 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces in evaporated milk and coat with crumb mixture. Place in single layer in shallow roasting pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 servings.
Per Serving:
235 calories, 39 g protein, 6 g carbohydrate, 5 g fat, 121 mg cholesterol and 317 mg sodium.

title: creamed mushrooms
directions: Wash, stem and slice mushrooms.
Slice stems and boil in 3/4 cup water for 8 to 10 minutes for mushroom stock.
Saute the sliced mushroom caps in 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Melt remaining butter or margarine; blend in flour and salt and slowly stir in the milk, half and half and mushroom stock.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Add sauteed mushrooms and sherry.

title: mabel's fruit salad
directions: Place all fruit and pecans in bowl.
Mix lemon instant pudding and 2 cups juice.
Blend and pour over fruit.
Chill. Other fruit may be used.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package. Set aside.

title: fruit cookie pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat together the butter and sugars until light and creamy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually blend into butter mixture until just moistened.
Press dough evenly into a 12-inch pizza pan. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and cool.

title: mini pizza muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Place muffins cut side up on baking sheet. Spread pizza sauce on muffins. Sprinkle cheese over sauce. Top with pepperoni slices and mushrooms (or other toppings of your choice). Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: apple and butternut squash soup
directions: Melt butter; cook onion with thyme for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, juice and garlic.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add broth and chickpeas.
Simmer for another 15 minutes.
Add cooked pasta and pepper.
Cook until warm.
Serve with Parmesan cheese on top.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients in kettle.
Cook over direct heat until thick and smooth.
Beat egg yolks and add to milk mixture. Boil 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; cool. (May add bananas, coconut, etc.).

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and drain hamburger meat.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to meat and simmer 2 hours.
Serve on buns.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into bottom of round cake pan.
Add brown sugar to cake pan, mix with butter and spread to coat bottom of cake pan.
Place pineapple rings around outside of cake pan, on top of brown sugar and place one pineapple ring in center.
Place 1 maraschino cherry in center of each pineapple ring.
Follow directions on cake mix and pour batter in cake pan.
You will have batter left over.
Bake as directed on cake box.
Allow to cool. Place plate on top of cake pan and turn over.

title: basic fruit wine(blackberry, elderberry, huckleberry)
directions: Wash fruit.
Put in large kettle and cover with water.
Cook until soft, but not mushy.
Strain juice through cloth.
Cool. Measure into stone or enamel crock or jar.
For each gallon of juice, add 2 to 3 pounds of sugar.
Mix 1 teaspoon of dry yeast into a paste and spread on half slice of bread.
Place yeast side down on juice.
When juice begins to foam, remove bread.
It will work several days.
Skim as needed.

title: orange breakfast rolls
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
In a bowl, sprinkle yeast over water.
Let set 5 minutes. Stir in 1/4 cup sugar, salt, sour cream, 6 tablespoons butter and eggs.
Add 1 3/4 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour to make soft dough. Cover and let rise 45 to 60 minutes.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, orange peel and 3/4 cup sliced nuts.
Set aside.
After setting, knead the dough, roll out, then cut in 1/2-inch slice rectangles.
Brush butter on them. Sprinkle with sugar.
Roll the rectangles in pan.
Let set and rise until doubled in size.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Put orange peel, nuts and sugar mix over top.
Bake for the rest of the time.

title: fast cookies
directions: Put sugar and syrup into a pan and let come to a boil.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Pour this mixture over corn flakes. Mix rapidly and flatten out on greased cookie sheet.
Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: aunt allie's apricot jello mold
directions: Combine jello
and
water
in
large bowl.
Add apricot nectar and mix well.
Pour 1/2 inch layer of this mixture into a
ring mold.
Decorate alternately with mandarin oranges and cherries. Place
in refrigerator and let set (1 hour).
Place bowl containing
remaining mixture in fridge until mixture is partially set.
Remove
from refrigerator and add 1/2 cup sour cream.
Beat with
rotary
beater.
Add remaining oranges and combine thoroughly.
Pour into mold and refrigerate to set.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar (or honey).
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil, then to that add flour mixture and mix by hand.
Put into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar.
Gradually add white sugar and continue creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk to cream mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour batter into a tube pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: birds' nest
directions: Form into small balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg whites. Roll in nuts; press hollow in center (using back of teaspoon). Bake 8 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and fill centers with jam or date-nut filling.
Return to oven.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Let stand a few minutes.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until done at 350° (about 15 minutes).
Keep in refrigerator.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread but don't let rise.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Tear one loaf into pan.
Stir rest of ingredients until smooth and pour over torn loaf.
Tear up second loaf on top of mixture.
Let rise for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes before turning rolls out of pan.

title: green beans
directions: In skillet, place 2 tablespoons oil and minced garlic and fry until lightly browned.
Add drained green beans, tomato juice and brown sugar.
Simmer until liquid thickens, about 1/2 hour.
Serve hot.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients for ten minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Cook California Blend until tender.
In a saucepan, mix cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Put vegetables in baking dish and pour sauce over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix first five ingredients well.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).
Mix melted butter and corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture. Bake for 45 minutes covered and another 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: chocolate caramel cookies
directions: Cream butter, 1 Cup of sugar and brown sugar in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture just until combined.
Shape dough by teaspoonfuls around each candy. Combine pecans and sugar.
Dip each cookie in half halfway.
Place with nut side up on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375 for 7 to 10 minutes or until top is slightly cracked.
Cool for 3 minutes before removing from sheet.
Move to rack to cool completely.

title: chicken salad(nice for a party.)
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, salt, mustard, pepper and lemon juice. Blend until smooth. Add chicken, grapes and celery. Toss well. Top with sliced almonds. Serve on bed of lettuce. Garnish with melon slices.

title: chewy turtle cake
directions: Pour boiling water on chocolate.
Melt and cool.
Grease and flour rectangle pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat in chocolate and vanilla on low speed.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt, alternating with buttermilk, beating after each addition until batter is smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter; pour in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Spread Caramel Topping over cake.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake about 20 minutes or until chips are melted.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Place 4 boneless chicken breasts in 13 x 19-inch pan.
Cover with 3 large slices of Swiss cheese.
Cover with 1 can of cream of chicken soup.
Cover with 8 oz.
Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix. Pour 1/2 Lb. melted Oleo over mix.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Add frozen strawberries; stir occasionally until thawed. Add pineapple and bananas. Stir in pecans. Pour half into 8X8 inch pan; chill until firm. Spread evenly with sour cream. Pour remaining gelatin on top chill until firm. Cut into 9 squares. Top each square with 1 Tbsp. sour cream.

title: mexican dip
directions: Arrange the bean dip as first layer on serving dish.
Mix together the avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread as second layer over bean dip.
Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise and dry taco mix.
Spread sour cream mixture as third layer over avocado mixture.
Chop up the tomato, olives and green onion and layer each on top.
Sprinkle the cheese, grated, as last ingredient on top of tomato, olives and onion.
Serve with taco chips.

title: homemade ice cream mix
directions: Cut up fruit such as strawberries or peaches may be added or Grape-Nuts which have been soaked or mashed bananas and cover with 2 cups of sugar before you make the mix.

title: refreshing summer cucumber salad
directions: Combine lemon jello and boiling water; let set until leathery but not set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix, then put in mold or 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at high speed of electric mixer until very thick (about 10 minutes).
Lower mixer speed to medium and gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in half and half, evaporated milk, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Add strawberries and stir in food coloring to desired color.
Pour mixture into container of a 1-gallon freezer. Fill to within 3 inches of top with milk.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen at least 2 hours.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine first eight ingredients. Shape into a 10 x 12-inch rectangle on wax paper. Sprinkle with cheese. Roll up and press ends to seal. Place in a shallow pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Pour 2/3 cup
tomato sauce over and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and rinse with cold water and then hot water, drain well and mix with oleo, parmesan and well beaten eggs, form into bottom and up sides of a 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese on top.

title: stuffed mushrooms(microwave)
directions: Dice and cook bacon on Full power for 4 minutes or until crisp.
Remove bacon and all but 2 tablespoons of drippings. Remove stems from mushrooms and chop stems finely.

title: prunes 'n cream pie
directions: Place prunes in bottom of pie shell.
Combine sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in the cream.
Pour mixture over prunes. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jars.
Add to each jar the following:
2 or 3 cloves garlic, 2 bay leaves, 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed and 2 or 3 red hot peppers (or 1 teaspoon loose red peppers).

title: pizza muffins
directions: Shred the cheeses.
Mix all ingredients together except tomato paste and muffins.
Spread tomato paste on muffin halves; then spread on topping mixture.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes. Topping mixture can be covered and refrigerated and used as needed.

title: champagne punch
directions: Stir the sugar with the brandy, maraschino and curacao to dissolve sugar.
Pour over block of ice in bowl.
Add and gently stir in champagne and mineral water.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: Melt oleo.
Stir in sugar and crumbs.
(Reserve 1/3 cup for topping.)
Pat crumbs in bottom of 9 X 13 baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: pumpkin corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan or muffin pan.
Stir together all ingredients; mix well, but don't overmix batter.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into pan.
Dump cherry pie filling on top. Spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix on top.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix.
Slice oleomargarine on top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Chop zucchini, onions and green and red bell pepper in big bowl.
Beat eggs.
Add Bisquick, baking powder, salt, Cheddar cheese and oil (last).
Add vegetable mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until tender.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a glass oven safe dish, place pork chops in a single layer.
Peel and slice potatoes and onion about 1/4-inch thick.
Layer potatoes, then break onions into rings and place on top of potatoes.
Glob celery soup on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and green pepper.
Add all other ingredients except 1/2 cup water and cornstarch.
Heat until boiling and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Combine remaining water and cornstarch.
Add to chili, a little at a time, stirring and cooking for 1 minute after each addition until you have reached the desired thickness.
Simmer up to 1/2 hour longer.
Freezes well.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of the meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato if desired.

title: easy quiche lorraine
directions: About 50 Minutes Before Serving:
Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat, cook bacon until browned. With slotted spoon, remove bacon to drain on paper towels. Sprinkle cheese and half of bacon in pie crust.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in half and half, salt and nutmeg.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 325° and bake 20 minutes longer, or until set.
Garnish with remaining bacon.

title: margaret's salad
directions: Drain peaches and cut in bite-size pieces.
Combine all ingredients together except bananas.
When ready to serve, cut up 3 bananas into salad and sprinkle with poppy seed.

title: chili con carne
directions: In Dutch oven, put ground chuck, onion, green pepper and celery on medium heat, stirring constantly, until meat is browned. Add cut up tomatoes, chili powder, tomato paste and sugar.
Mix well.
Let mixture come to a boil. Turn stove on low and cook for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add kidney beans and cook 15 minutes longer.
Stir to mix well.
Remove from heat and serve over rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in salted water until tender; drain.
Add grated cheese and butter.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Add crushed crackers.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and press down.

title: chicken breasts with chipped beef
directions: Layer a casserole dish with chipped beef.
Put chicken breasts on top of chipped beef.
Pour sour cream and soup mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for an hour or more.
Serve with rice and use the gravy on the rice.

title: french tourtiere("canadian pork pie")
directions: Prepare pastry for 2 (9-inch) double-crust pies.

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw bread.
Cut each loaf in 40 pieces.
Dip the pieces in the melted butter.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Place balls side by side in greased Bundt pan.
Let raise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple ham balls
directions: In a bowl, combine ham, pork, bread crumbs, eggs and pepper; mix well.
Chill.
Form into 10 balls and set aside.
Drain the pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup of juice.
Place juice in a saucepan with sugar, vinegar and dry mustard.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.

title: dilly dip
directions: Blend all of the ingredients until well mixed. Can be served at once, but it is better if made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to use. Serve as a dip with raw vegetables.

title: ziti
directions: Cook and drain ziti noodles.
Mix with jar of spaghetti sauce; set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, 6 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese. Place one half of ziti mixture in the bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spoon Ricotta mixture on top.
Cover with remaining ziti mixture and sprinkle with remaining shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 28 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in the eggs and bananas.
In another bowl, sift together the flour and soda.
Add alternately with the buttermilk to the other mixture. Add the pecans.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: snack time taco dip(a favorite of mary sue and bruce lambert)
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch square glass dish, spread 1 can of refried beans on the bottom evenly.
Pit and mash the avocados; mix with the lemon juice with a dash of salt and pepper.
Spread on top of the refried beans.
Mix the mayo, sour cream and the taco seasoning well; spread on top of the avocado mixture.
Chop the tomatoes, onions and
olives and sprinkle alternately with the cheese on top of the sour cream mixture.
Serve with taco chips. (Note:
Long periods of refrigeration may cause sogginess.)
Eat with the taco chips or just a spoon.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute broccoli and onion in 1/4 cup butter for 10 minutes. Combine soup, water and rice.
Add broccoli mix.
Stir in pieces of cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°; stir before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition. Stir in flavorings.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Frost with White Mountain Frosting.
Sprinkle coconut between layers, top and sides of cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugars together. Add eggs and beat.
Stir in applesauce and zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Stir in orange juice, water and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased, floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Stir in chicken, 1 cup cheese, sour cream, hot sauce and pepper.
Roll biscuits out to 1/4 to 1/8-inch thick.
Spread 2 tablespoons of mixture on each rolled biscuit.
Roll biscuits up and seal by pressing dough together.
Place biscuits in greased baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Combine soup and milk in saucepan.
Heat and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over all.
Bake for 3 to 5 more minutes.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring to boil the oleo and water.
Remove from heat and add flour; mix.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix.
Spread dough on greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in loaf pan.
Cover top lightly with catsup.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first three ingredients in pan and cook until it makes a soft ball in cold water, then add last 2 ingredients and stir well into mixture.
Beat until hardened.

title: kookie brittle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/4-inch.
In large mixer bowl, cream oleo; add salt and vanilla. Beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and continue mixing until well combined.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pat dough into greased pan with hands.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly brown at edges.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
When cool, break with hands into pieces.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a large pan, saute onions, garlic and green pepper in butter until soft.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.
Add your favorite meat, shredded, and cook very low for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oven chicken linguini
directions: Melt butter in a 12 x 15-inch pan in 400° oven.
Mix onion, garlic, basil and chilies into butter.
Lay chicken on top of butter and seasonings.
Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes, add spinach to butter and seasonings, toss well.
Cook pasta in boiling water for 13 minutes.
Add to spinach mixture and cover cooked chicken with it.
Sprinkle with cheese to serve.

title: no butter - butter cookies
directions: Cream the first 6 ingredients together.
Let stand 10 minutes and then add flour and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
This dough can be made into rolls, chilled and then sliced and baked.
It can be chilled and then rolled out for Christmas cutouts.
It can also be dropped by teaspoon and baked.
Cookies can be decorated with nuts, cherries or colored sugar before baking.
A great basic cookie recipe! Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange flavored carrots
directions: Add carrots, onion and salt to boiling water.
Cover and simmer until carrots are tender.
Drain and save 2 tablespoons of cooking liquid.
Add orange juice concentrate, lemon juice and cooking liquid.
Stir.
Heat again until vegetables are hot.

title: ham with pineapple sauce
directions: Cover top of ham with a thick layer of brown sugar.
Pour juice of pineapple over ham and arrange pineapple on ham.
Add ginger ale.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting at least 3 times.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins until done.
Cut into cubes after cooked.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble over potatoes when done. Add chopped onion.
Prepare Hidden Valley dressing according to directions and pour over all.
Stir together and serve.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Stir soup, sour cream, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine cornflake crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 20 minutes more (until browned). Serves 12.

title: peggy's easy punch
directions: Leave sherbet at room temperature for about 30 minutes.
Put in mixing bowl and add ginger ale.
Chop with vegetable chopper until desired consistency.
Pour into punch bowl and serve. Serves 20.

title: taco pie
directions: Mix hamburger meat and taco seasoning.
Cook until brown and drain.
Add sour cream and stir.
Set aside.

title: west texas spaghetti
directions: Saute meat with green pepper and onion.
Stir to cook and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato soup.
Let simmer 30 minutes.

title: bacon poles
directions: Coat one side of each bacon slice half with cheese.
Wrap each bread stick with one bacon slice half in spiral fashion, cheese side toward bread stick.
Place on a microwave-safe plate lined with 3 paper towels.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes (until bacon is crisp), rotating plate halfway through cooking.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt oleo.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix. Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar with mixer until smooth.
Spoon over graham cracker.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: light whole wheat hotcakes
directions: Combine in the order given.
Fold in egg whites last.
This is a sweeter than usual hotcake recipe; sugar can be reduced if desired.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add to the pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.
Cut into bars.

title: norwegian bread
directions: Beat eggs, add mashed sweet potatoes.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Add water slowly.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bread will crack on top.
This is good with cream cheese spread on after you slice it.

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot and simmer 15 minutes. Serve over pasta.

title: apricot nut balls
directions: Mix. Roll in pecans and powdered sugar.

title: taco rice skillet
directions: Brown beef and onion in 10-inch skillet; drain off fat.
Drain and cut up tomatoes, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add tomatoes, liquid, rice and taco seasoning to beef in skillet.
Stir.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Top with shredded lettuce and cheese before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Cream together butter and sugar in large bowl.
Peel ripe bananas and mash until no lumps remain.
Blend egg into creamed sugar/butter mixture and then mix mashed bananas.

title: ginger pickles
directions: Slice the cukes thin and cover with cold water in which the salt has been dissolved to 1 gallon of water. Soak 8 days. Drain and rinse in cold water.

Add the alum to cukes. Cover with water and boil 1/2 hour. Drain and cover with water. Add the ginger and boil 1/2 hour. Drain and add the remaining ingredients. Boil until clear, about 1/2 hour. Can.

title: peanut hot dish
directions: Cut up onions and celery.
Add about 1 tablespoon of water and cook in microwave until done.
In greased casserole, put all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: veggie pita pockets
directions: In bowl, combine meat, broccoli, cauliflower, tomato, carrot, cucumber and onion.
Toss with dressing.
Cover and chill several hours.
Spoon mixture into pocket bread; sprinkle each with shredded cheese.
Serves 8.

title: creamy chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Place a slice of Swiss cheese over each piece of chicken.
Mix soup and wine; pour over chicken evenly.
Sprinkle herb stuffing (dry) evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Delicious with rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni cheese bake(diabetic)
directions: Combine evaporated milk and dry milk; heat over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a casserole dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Counts as 1 milk, 1 1/2 fats, 1 bread and 1 protein.
Makes 2 servings.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Grind meat, then mix with meat stock, garlic, onion, chili powder, comino and salt to taste.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Stir in olives. Make a stiff mush by scalding cornmeal with boiling water and 1 tablespoon of salt.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, blending well.
Stir in applesauce; mix well.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters into desired shapes.
Insert horseshoe wire shape into cookie shapes or put hole in with straw to hang.
Let ornaments dry 4 to 5 days uncovered.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix. Store in tightly covered jar.
Makes 2 cups mix.
Use approximately 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar. Add flour and soda.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, pecans and raisins.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and chop.
Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients together and add to the other mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in chopped apples.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add nuts, if used.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and bananas.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla only until flour is moistened.
Bake in a greased 9 x 5-inch pan at 350° for an hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix sliced cucumbers, onion, peppers, garlic and salt.
Cover with crushed ice; let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cool and serve.

title: easy oven roast beef
directions: Sprinkle dry soup mix onto large sheet of aluminum foil. Place meat on soup mix.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour soup over meat.
Add garlic.
Seal foil.
Place sealed foil on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
(A super easy, super delicious roast that is good for family or company!)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kaese kuchen (cheese pie)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and chop.
Discard all but 2 tbsp grease.
Saute onion in this until tender.
Heat milk, add slightly beaten eggs.
Mix with remainder of ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Preheat oven to 425.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Turn the temp. down to 350 and continue baking until set and lightly browned on top, about 35- 45 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes 3/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dredge with flour or dip in beaten egg and roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in small amount of butter, turning to brown on both sides.

title: cattle clatter hash
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Add chili powder, salt, garlic and blended tomatoes; simmer.
Cook the macaroni and combine with meat mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Add grated cheese and pour mushroom soup over top.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: I usually use strawberry gelatin.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Mix meal, sugar, corn, oil and milk.
Pour this in a well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle black pepper on corn meal mixture.
Pour onion mixed with sour cream on top of cornbread.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no trot chili company blue ribbon recipe
directions: Cut beef into 1 cubes and mix with pork, onion and garlic and cook in 1 Tbsp. oil until brown and tender.
Add tomatoes; continue to cook on low heat.
Dissolve bouillon and brown sugar in two cups hot water and set aside.
Heat remainder of oil in a pan; add chili powder, flour and pepper.
Cook until flour is brown, then add bouillon mix, stirring constantly until blended. Add the Roux to the meat; blend and cook on low heat for one hour.

title: hot turnip green dip
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add well drained and thawed greens; add lemon rind.
Process until finely chopped. Cook onion and celery in butter over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir in greens, mushrooms and rest of ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until all is mixed and melted together.
Serve from a chafing dish.
Serve with Jalapeno Corn Muffins (recipe found in this book).
Yields 3 cups.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Run cold water until noodles are cool. Add seasoning packages and mix well.
Add onion, carrot, olives and other veggies.
Mix well.
Spoon noodle mixture into rectangular serving dish.
Spread mayonnaise on top; just enough to coat.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough on a lightly floured surface; press seams and perforations together.
Roll into a 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread sausage to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Sprinkle with chives.
Carefully roll up from a long side; cut into 12 slices.
Place 1-inch apart on an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 16 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Put cranberries and sugar in pan and cover with foil. Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Cool a little; then add marmalade, ginger and pecans, in layers, with pecans on top.
