Refrigerate and use as condiment with turkey. OR serve as a dessert with whipped cream or possibly with vanilla ice cream. If it is too gingery, cut amount in half.

title: lime jello dessert
directions: Mix lemon Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and soft cream cheese.
Let set until firm.
Mix lime Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water; mix in pineapple juice and all . Pour on top of lemon; let set.
Looks pretty in clear glass bowl or great for mold.
Put lime on bottom for Christmas.
Looks great, tastes better.

title: fish camp slaw
directions: Combine and mix well.
Pack into a quart jar and a 1/2 pint jar.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: cheesy corn bake
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: ground cherry pie
directions: Boil the ingredients on top of the stove until syrup is thick. Pour in unbaked pie shells (double crust).
Bake at 375° to 400° for 20 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° for 20 more minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zesty bread pudding
directions: Put one slice of bread in blender at a time to get 7 cups of crumbs.
Mix milk, eggs, sugar and margarine in bowl and add bread and other ingredients to mixture.
Bake in greased dish at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Let lemonade thaw until it shakes in can.
Mix together with milk and Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix crabmeat, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Form this mixture into a ball, then pour cocktail sauce over it for the finishing touch.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fancy crab dip
directions: Whip cheese and cream together.
Add minced onion, catsup, salt and mayonnaise; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Keep refrigerated until used.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine well beaten eggs, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and salt until well blended, slowly beat
in milk.
Gently fold in whipped cream, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Also,
rum
may be added to taste.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones.
Add rice, soup, broth, celery and onion.
Mix and bake slowly for one hour.

title: cream of chicken and cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken broth.
Add chopped meat, soup, Velveeta. and milk.
Heat, stirring often as it scorches easily. Don't add salt to chicken when cooking as Velveeta adds plenty of salt.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large bowl.
Pour marinade over vegetables and mix. Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours, stirring 3-4 times to mix well. Drain before serving.

title: cheesy enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, chili powder, and sauce.
Cook on stove for 5 minutes.
Add a little water if it starts to dry out.
Place four tortilla shells on baking sheet.
Put 1/4 cup cheese inside each shell.
Add 2 Tbsp. of meat mixture per shell.
Fold shells and add 1/4 cup cheese on top of each shell.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese is melted.

title: quiche lorraine(cheese custard pie)
directions: Heat oven to 424°.
Line glass pie plate with rich pastry; fold edges under and press to rim with fork.
Bake for 5 minutes. Prick with fork if it puffs up.
Mix cheese and flour.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and pour off fat.
Separate onion into rings; cook in butter in same pan.
Spread cheese in partially baked pie shell; sprinkle with bacon and onion.
Beat eggs lightly; add milk, cream and seasonings.
Pour into pastry.
Jiggle pan to settle liquid.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° (moderate).
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, until custard sets. Cool 10 minutes before cutting. Serve as main dish or appetizer.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple (save juice). Cut bananas, apples and oranges in small pieces. Add to other fruit. Add grapes, cherries and nuts. Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone and cut in pieces.
Place in a 7 x 11-inch buttered dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Crush crackers; sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt oleo; dribble on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Soak cereal and milk for 10 minutes.
Add egg and sifted dry ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Put in loaf pan.
Let rise for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased pan, use butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tortilla beef bake
directions: Cook ground beef and chiles. Drain.
Stir in soup.
In a shallow, 2 1/2 quart greased baking dish, sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of tortilla chips.
Top chips with beef mixture.
Add salsa and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle the remaining chips over the top of the casserole.
Bake for 5 minutes longer or until chips are brown. Cool for a few minutes before serving.

title: cherry salad
directions: Add water to pie filling and boil 5 minutes.
Add box of cherry gelatin while first mixture is still hot.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, add pineapple, chopped pecans and cola.
Pour into dish and chill.

title: shrimp spread
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in ReaLemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill to blend flavors.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Drain and slice or chop water chestnuts. Place vegetables and chestnuts into a 3-quart mixing bowl.
Add chicken soup, onion, celery and mayonnaise; mix well.
Pour into a 2 or 3-quart casserole.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until bubbly and cracker crumbs are medium brown.

title: m z's crushed pineapple cake
directions: Mix jiffy cake according to package directions using a greased and floured 13x9-inch pan baking at 350°, let cool.
Beat the cream cheese till smooth.
Slowly add the cold milk, continue beating, add the vanilla pudding, and beat till thick.
Pour over cooled cake.
Spread the drained crushed pineapple on top of the pudding/cream cheese mixture.
Top with cool whip.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: embezzlers special
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix in soup, salt and pepper. Serve over noodles.

title: paper wrapped chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the oil and marinate 20 to
30 minutes.
Divide the mixture into 16 portions and wrap each portion
in
aluminum foil and fasten well.
Heat oil in wok to 375° and deep fry the packages a few at a time for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain
on
paper	toweling
and keep hot.
Do not reheat.
Serve
wrapped to hold in the tasty juice.
The diner unwraps each just before eating.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Stir and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch together and heat until it forms a syrup.
Arrange berries in baked crust.
Pour syrup over berries.
Top with cream just before serving.

title: new orleans shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce. Toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly and serve on lettuce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: beef macaroni casserole
directions: Mix beef, milk, eggs, ketchup, onion and salt.
Set aside.
Mix cooked macaroni, mustard, green pepper and mayonnaise.
Spread this mixture in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Spread beef mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese; top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Place tomato slices on top and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Whip cream cheese and margarine; mix and blend sugar, cream cheese, margarine and pecans until smooth.
Spread between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: lacy molasses roll-ups
directions: Combine sugar, molasses, water and butter or margarine in large saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, just to boiling.
Cool slightly.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into small bowl; stir in walnuts to coat well.
(Be sure walnuts have been chopped finely or cookies will crack when rolled.)
Stir into molasses mixture just until blended.
(Mixture will be very thin.) Drop by scant tablespoons 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheets. (Make only 6 cookies at a time for easy handling.
To save time, use two cookie sheets and bake one batch while shaping the other.) Bake in slow oven at 325° for 10 minutes or until a rich dark brown.
Cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients;
form into a ball and roll in nuts. Chill.

title: party pizza ryes
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, sausage, onion, green pepper and Italian seasoning.
Drain off fat; return to skillet. Add cubed Velveeta, Mozzarella and enough garlic powder to taste. Stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Spread 1 large teaspoon of mixture onto each party rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mystery pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk together until smooth.
Spread in a graham cracker crust.
Cover with 1 cup chopped pecans, then cover with strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: carol's hush puppies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Using a large spoon, cut sections of mix and drop in heated oil.
Simmer until golden brown.

title: dinner in a skillet
directions: Place pork chops in electric skillet.
Slice onions on top of pork chops.
Slice potatoes on top of onions and pork chops.
Add 1 cup of water and cook at 350° until done, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate mallow pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk until smooth. Add pudding mix and remaining milk. Mix well. Fold in the marshmallows. Pour into the crust. Refrigerate until serving. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: cappuccino fudge
directions: Line 9-inch square or 9 x 13-inch pan with foil, extending foil over sides.
Butter foil.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add oatmeal add other dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts, chocolate chips and raisins.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine
cooked broccoli, rice, soup and 1/2 cup onions in
a 2 quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until hot.
Microwave cheese spread according to
label
directions.
Stir
cheese
spread
into broccoli mixture;
top
with
remaining
onions.
Microwave 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: philly cheese steak
directions: Slice mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Put into pan with the butter.
Saute.
While all of that sautes, slice the London broil very thin, almost see through.
Add to the rest.
Cook until meat is done.
Then add all of the cheese.
Cook until it melts.
Serve on a soft hoagie roll.

title: cottage cheese - orange salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Drain pineapple and oranges. Add them to first mixture; chill for several hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, peanut butter together.
Add vanilla and eggs; then dry ingredients.
Roll in small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten gently with fork dipped in flour. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: 5 minute lemonade pie
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients until blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Serve with pie filling on top, if desired.
So easy to make, kids can do it!

title: wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a pint of sympathy and understanding. Flavor with loving companionship.
Bake well, all your life. Frost with kisses and fond hopes for the future.
Cake keeps well and can be served often.

title: alvena's fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit and juices together.
Add pudding and Tang.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake in uncovered baking dish at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: When using unsweetened chocolate squares instead of cocoa, melt 2 (1 ounce) squares in 1 3/4 cups scalded milk spoken of in recipe.

title: clams in cream sauce
directions: Drain clams; reserve juice.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix milk and cornstarch.
Blend thoroughly.
Add to saucepan.
Stir constantly.
Add clam juice.
Stir until thickened.
Add grated cheese and parsley.
Remove from heat.
In skillet, saute garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add clams.
Cook until warm.
Add to cream sauce.

title: spinach-romaine salad
directions: Cut or tear romaine lettuce and spinach.

title: enchiladas
directions: Combine enchilada mix, tomato juice and chili (without beans); set aside.
Brown hamburger; drain and let cool.
Add onion, olives and 1/2 of shredded cheese.
Dip tortillas in the tomato juice mixture.
Put meat mixture in tortilla and roll up.
Place side by side in baking pan.
Pour leftover sauce over tortillas; top with remaining shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach, then squeeze out excess water.
Stir in Miracle Whip, sour cream, onions and bacon bits.
Serve with any kind of cracker.

title: barbecue rice
directions: Cook rice. In skillet, cook onion in butter and all soups. Then add all in baking dish, mixing well. Add enough broth to make juicy. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes.

title: quick and hearty gumbo
directions: Cook sausage in large saucepan, about 4 minutes, drain. Stir in tomatoes, broth and 1/2 cup water; bring to boil.
Stir in corn and rice, cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Serve with cornbread or biscuits, if desired.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Line crust with bananas.
Mix softened cream cheese with the sugar.
Whip cream and add to cheese and sugar.
Pour this over the bananas and top with blueberries with the lemon juice in them. Chill.

title: balsamic vinegar marinade
directions: Place meat in mixture; let sit 1 hour.
Baste meat with mixture while cooking.
After initial marinade, the mixture can be thickened to taste to be used as a sauce to be served with the meat.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook bacon and onions in 3-quart saucepan; drain.
Remove from pan.
In same pan, bring water to boil.
Add potatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, over medium heat 18 minutes.
Stir in sauce mix, milk, parsley, pepper, bacon and onions.
Simmer over medium heat, 4 to 5 minutes or until desired consistency.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: rosy wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring almost to simmering.
Add 1 bottle of Sauterne and heat.
Do not boil.
Stir in a few drops of red food coloring.

title: barbee's zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add to zucchini mix and blend.
Add nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: luke's no bake fruitcake
directions: In a large double boiler, melt oleo, marshmallows and juice of cherries.
In a large mixing bowl, mix the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well, then pour in liquid mixture; mix well, then press into tube cake pan or into baking cups for individual servings.
Decorate cake or cupcakes with pecan halves or cherry halves.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan and cook at low boil with lid on for about 30 minutes.
Use as a sauce for cooked meat.

title: cherry cream dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or large bowl and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving. May store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and cut flowerets into bite size pieces. Layer lettuce, onion, cauliflower and bacon in 3-quart bowl. Combine mayonnaise and sugar and mix well.
Spread evenly over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover salad tightly and refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss gently before serving.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Combine in saucepan; cook until sugar is dissolved.
Continue to cook until 238°.
Remove from heat and add nuts; stir gently until creamy.
Turn onto wax paper.
Separate nuts.
Let dry.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine cinnamon and applesauce to form a stiff dough.
Add additional applesauce if necessary.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Make a hole with a straw at the top.
Carefully place on wire rack or in dehydrator to dry. Let air dry several days, turning occasionally.
Makes 12 sweet smelling ornaments.
Great for kids!

title: cottage cheese and noodles
directions: Chop bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Boil noodles until done and drain.
Add container cottage cheese and fried bacon bits.
Mix and serve.

title: wow it's squash
directions: Pour melted oleo over stuffing.
Mix well.
Mix together the squash, onions, sour cream and soup.
Stir in half the stuffing mix.
Pour into baking dish and cover with remainder of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Place 3 cups peaches in pie shell.
Combine 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and salt.
Add eggs and sour cream, stirring until well-blended.
Spoon over peaches.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and remaining flour.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
(Using a pastry blender works best.)
Sprinkle evenly over pie.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Use sliced peaches for garnish.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put chicken in a good size pot.
Add enough water to cover. Simmer slowly over a small fire to draw out as much of the juices as possible.
Add onion, salt and tomato, then cook again until these are tender.
When ready the flesh will fall of the bones. Serve hot.

title: apple-cinnamon snack mix
directions: Combine first four ingredients and spread on a greased baking sheet.
In a small mixing bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over dry ingredients, stirring to coat well.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes, stirring frequently to break apart.
Pour onto waxed paper to cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, thyme and pepper. Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.

title: pea pickin' cake(makes large loaf or 3 layers)
directions: Bake cake as directed on cake box.
Cool well.

title: pineapple slices
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in lukewarm milk; set aside.
Sift, then measure flour.
Add shortening as in pie crust; mix well. Add milk, eggs and mix into flour mixture.
Divide dough into 2 parts and roll to fit pan (about 12 x 14-inch).
Spread filling on dough and let rise for about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place greens in the bottom of large glass bowl. Add celery, radishes, scallions, bacon and peas in individual layers. Carefully spread mayo over peas, completely covering the top and sealing to the edge of the bowl. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover salad tightly and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: rhubarb-strawberry jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and pineapple together and boil 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in jello.
Mix well.
Pour into hot jars.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cut cake in 4 layers; sprinkle with rum.
Mix together strawberries, pineapple chunks, bananas and any fresh fruit in season.
Sprinkle fruit with sugar to form juice.
Make vanilla pudding.

title: bicentennial gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients over creamed mixture and blend well.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: jambalaya
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, stir flour and oil until brown.
Add sausage, ham, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook about 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes until rice is tender.
Start with only half of V-8 juice. Add remaining according to desired thickness.
I use entire amount.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt and fat. Drain and rinse in cold water and drain again.
Combine macaroni and chicken in a large bowl; set aside.

title: broccoli-cheese potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes for about 5 minutes.
While they are cooking, saute butter and onion in a baking dish in the microwave. Heat the milk and soup together.
When the potatoes are ready, pour into baking dishes and pour the soup mixture over the potatoes.
Bake in the microwave, uncovered, for about 25 minutes or until the potatoes are done.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cut up stewed chicken into small pieces.
Cook broccoli until fork-tender.
Layer chicken, broccoli and Velveeta cheese.
Pour over the top the cream of chicken soup and milk.
Mix stuffing as directed on box.
Put on top and bake 45 minutes, covered with foil, then 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Use a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: swedish brownies
directions: Mix sugar and melted margarine.
Add and mix all other ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco hot dish
directions: Brown the hamburger and add onion, salt, pepper and taco seasoning with water.
Combine with soups, enchilada sauce and chilies. Heat.
Place in casserole, alternating layers of chips, sauce
and cheese. Bake until bubbly at 300°.
Serve with more chips.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken with onion and seasonings.
Cool, debone and chop. Cook pasta in broth from chicken; drain.
Add Velveeta, English peas, drained mushrooms and undrained Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add chicken.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour boiling water over cut up dates and butter; set aside until cool.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Bake in cake pan at 350°. Cut in small squares.

title: never fail swiss fudge
directions: Place milk, sugar and butter into saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until boiling.
Then cook for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire.
Gradually stir in chocolate and marshmallows.
Add vanilla and nutmeats.
Pour into greased pan to set.
Cut into generous squares.

title: toffee
directions: Line the pan with foil.
Spread a single layer of saltines to cover.
Dissolve sugar in butter.
Boil for exactly 3 minutes. Spread on saltines and bake in 400° oven for 7 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
When softened spread evenly to cover.
Sprinkle with walnuts and refrigerate.
When chilled, break into pieces.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix together, adding Rice Krispies last.
Make small balls and press with a fork.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° approximately 10 minutes.
Makes about 40 wafers.

title: fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add butter, milk and vanilla. Add pecans.
Press into pan and slice.

title: meat puffs
directions: Melt fat in skillet; add onions.
Saute until golden brown. Crumble bread into mixing bowl; add milk.
Let stand until bread is moist.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add onion, green pepper and salt. Add meat; mix well.
Pile mixture lightly into greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pans.
Top each with thin onion slice.
Bake in hot oven (425°) until nicely browned, about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook macaroni and add all other ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: hot sauce
directions: In blender, chop jalapenos and cilantro.
Put in large bowl. Chop onions and tomatoes.
Mix all together.
Salt to taste.

title: baked scallops and mushrooms in garlic sauce
directions: Rinse the scallops in cold water and pat dry with paper towels.
Remove the stems from the mushrooms and reserve both the stems and the caps.

Brush a shallow 8 to 9-inch diameter baking dish with 1 tablespoon of the olive oil; preheat the oven to 350°. Toss the scallops with the flour and arrange them with the mushroom caps in a single layer in the dish.
Pour the wine into the dish along the edge.
Finely chop the mushroom stems and mix them with the bread crumbs, onion, parsley, garlic, pepper flakes and salt.
Sprinkle this mixture over the scallops and mushrooms. Drizzle with the remaining olive oil.
Bake in the heated oven until the mushrooms are soft and scallops are cooked thoroughly, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
To reheat, loosely cover with foil and bake for about 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cocoa pink cuplets
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla and soda to creamed mixture.
Add water alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped nuts (optional) over batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese on top a few minutes before done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together until crumbs.
Sprinkle sugar and peanut butter crumbs over cooled pie shell, reserving 1/2 cup for topping.

title: coconut cherry chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, margarine, 1 cup coconut, almond extract and egg at low speed until well mixed and dough forms.
In small bowl, beat egg white and water until foamy. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip in egg white mixture; roll in coconut.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Place cherry in center of each cookie, pressing down lightly.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 14 minutes, or until edges are light golden brown. Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
corn syrup and margarine in double boiler. Bring to
boil.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Gradually add boiling mixture to
eggs,
stir in pecans, salt and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate peppermint sensation cake
directions: Grease and flour bundt cake pan.
Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat until well blended, approximately 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: hot shrimp scampi
directions: Saute garlic in oil in a large, heavy skillet over medium heat for 1 minute; do not burn.
Add chili pepper and shrimp; cook 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add lime juice and cook just until the shrimp are done.
Serve with rice or pasta.
Serves 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles while browning ground beef.
Drain both.
Chop onion and bell pepper into small pieces.
In skillet, mix together tomato sauce and spices, increasing or decreasing spices according to taste.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper and ground beef.
Simmer for about 3 minutes.
Shred Mozzarella cheese.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and then sprinkle with cheese.

title: dutch honey
directions: Bring sugar, cream and Karo syrup to a boil.
Cook for about 7 to 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Store in refrigerator and heat as needed.
Good on waffles, pancakes, pound cake, ice cream, etc. Keeps several weeks.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Pour water into a saucepan, add butter and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; add flour (all at once), stirring rapidly.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and leaves sides of the pan, about one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Beat until mixture looks satiny and breaks off when spoon is raised.

title: teen-agers delight
directions: Cook chopped onion in fat until golden brown. Add hamburger meat, salt and pepper. Cook until all meat is done. Add Worcestershire sauce, catsup, mustard, celery (if desired), tomato soup, chili powder and Italian seasoning. Cover. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve on rice or toasted buns. Good for buffets.

title: curry chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Reserve 1 cup of chicken broth. Cut meat in chunks and place in 14 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Cover with cooked broccoli.
Mix soup, reserved broth, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with dressing mix.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Yum Yum.)

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Place shrimp in baking dishes in single layer.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over shrimp.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: country-style ribs
directions: Place spareribs in 4 to 6-quart Dutch oven.
Add enough salted water to cover; bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until ribs are tender.
Drain.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat oven to 300°.

title: fat-free crab salad
directions: Let imitation crab thaw out if frozen.
Chop into bite-size pieces.
Drain can of crab and add to chopped crab.
Mix into crab the celery and fat-free mayonnaise and salt and pepper. Serve with saltines.

title: hash pizza pies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; spread to edge of muffin half.
Top with cheese slices.
Broil as far from heat as possible until cheese melts and pizza is bubbly hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in halves lengthwise; carefully remove yolks.
Mash yolks.
Add ingredients, except paprika.
Spoon or pipe into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 12 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; add grated cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix in hash brown potatoes.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together corn flakes and 1/2 stick margarine.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hoosier apple-yogurt coffee cake
directions: *Start with 1 2/3 cups oats; grind in blender or food processor.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.

title: apricot salad souffle
directions: Drain juice from apricots and add water to make 1 cup liquid. Heat to boiling; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and salt.
Blend in cream cheese until smooth. Chill until partially congealed.
Beat gelatin mixture until fluffy.
Fold in fruits, mayonnaise and almonds.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with sugared grapes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: strawberry crunch dessert
directions: Blend flour, butter and brown sugar; add nuts.
Put mixture on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° or until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Place crumbs on bottom of an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish, reserving a few for top.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Slice 1 package of the cookie dough and line the bottom of a 9 x 14-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla extract; add cream cheese and mix well.
Pour over cookies in pan.
Slice other roll of cookie dough, place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: minestrone (meatless)(low in fat, crock-pot recipe)
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot except zucchini.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 16 hours (high 4 to 6 hours).
During last hour, add zucchini.
Turn crock-pot to high and cook 1 hour.
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Place in large, flat dish.
Pour buttermilk over chicken; cover and allow to soak at least 1 hour or overnight in the refrigerator.
Combine coating ingredients in double strength paper bag.
Shake chicken pieces one at a time. Lay coated pieces on wax paper for 15 minutes to allow coating to dry.
Pour oil to 1/2 inch depth in electric skillet.
Heat to 350° to 360°.
Fry about 3 minutes on each side.
Reduce heat to 320°.
Cook chicken, turning occasionally, for 25 to 35 minutes or until juices are clear and chicken is tender.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Save 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top.
Line a large cake pan (9 x 13-inch).

title: mom's old fashioned punch
directions: Mix together.
Can be made ahead of time, however, do not add ginger ale and sherbet until right before serving.
Ice mold optional.
Yield: 164 ounces (42 servings).

title: garlic cheese spread
directions: Beat all ingredients in blender until light and fluffy. Spread on split French loaves.
Broil until spread is bubbly and brown.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together; will harden when chilled.
I serve on rye rounds or crackers.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add nuts, dates, coconut and well beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Spread the mixture about 1/2-inch thick in a buttered pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove pan from oven.
Cut in strips while still warm and roll in granulated sugar or roll in balls, then in sugar.

title: chicken maraffi
directions: Slice boneless chicken breasts (uncooked) into chunks.
Roll generously in seasoned bread crumbs.
Brown lightly in oil or margarine. Do this quickly so as not to cook chicken. Drain on paper towels.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat and season to taste.
Place in mixing bowl and add spaghetti sauce and cheese as well as cottage cheese. Add 8 ounces of water to mixture.

title: anita's pickled okra
directions: Soak okra in ice water for 1 hour.
Use the remaining ingredients per pint jar.
Put in jar.
Pack in okra and fill jar with approximately 1 cup boiling vinegar.
Seal jar with a lid and ring.
Let season at least 3 weeks.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: scotch shortbread cookies
directions: Roll out on floured cutting area about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 300° oven.
Ice and decorate.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, Jell-O and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool.
Slice peaches into pie shell. Pour cooled mixture over peaches.
Refrigerate.
Add Cool Whip to serve.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir in mayonnaise and hot pepper sauce.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Yields 10 servings.
Contains 217 calories.
Diabetic Exchange: 2 breads and 1 1/2 fat.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Saute flour and oil until brown.
Add onion, garlic, celery, parsley and green onion.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup water, salt and pepper and Tabasco.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Stir in shrimp and cook covered for 5 minutes.
Serve over hot creamy rice.
Serves 4.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks.
Fry bacon and remove from skillet. Saute diced onion in bacon fat.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper, celery seed and sugar.
Cook over low heat, stir until smooth. Remove from heat and stir in water and vinegar.
Pour over warm potatoes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon.
Fry in oil until brown on both sides and cooked through middle.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Chill all ingredients as cold as possible and blend until smooth.
Makes 2 (12-ounce) servings.

title: *spinach with rice
directions: Saute the onions in heated oil until golden.
Add the spinach which has been thoroughly washed and drained. Add a little water and bring to a boil.
Sprinkle the parsley and dill and add the washed rice.
Stir.
Season to taste and allow to simmer for about 15 minutes or until tender.
Can be served with meat, fish or poultry or alone with cheese.

title: muscadine sauce
directions: Wash muscadines.
Separate hulls and pulp.
Cut hulls in half or grind in a food chopper.
Add a small amount water to hulls and cook over low heat 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Heat hulls and pulp.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer until mixture is thick.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.
Yield: About 13 pints.
Very good with meat or used as jelly.

title: meat casserole
directions: In saucepan, brown the meat with the onion.
Add in the syrup, tomato sauce, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cook noodles as package directs.
Add almonds to sauce mixture.
In 2-quart baking dish, arrange in alternate layers the noodles, the meat and the grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: duncan hines devils food, swiss chocolate and dark dutch fudge(microwave)
directions: Empty cake mix into large bowl.
Add eggs, hot water and Crisco oil.
Mix well with fork or wire whisk until smooth and thick (about 200 strokes).
Pour half of batter into a microwave safe cake pan.

If a small pan is used, do not pour more than half full. Microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes, longer for low wattage ovens. Cake is done when it pulls away from sides of dish and top is dry. If not done, continue baking at 30 seconds intervals.
Bake only 1 layer at a time.
De-pan immediately.
Cool 5 to 15 minutes and frost (small wet spots on top of cake will finish cooking during cooling time).
Cover tightly.

title: ham and bean vegetable soup
directions: Rinse beans.
In a 4-quart Dutch oven, combine beans and water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cover.
Let stand 1 hour (or soak beans in the water overnight in a covered pan).
Do not drain!

title: oatmeal, peanut butter, raisin cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well. Add eggs and vanilla mixing well.

title: apple and zucchini salad
directions: Combine salad oil, lemon juice, vinegar, sugar, basil, 3/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Add the apples and coat well with the dressing.
Thinly slice the onion lengthwise and distribute over apples.
Arrange layer of green pepper and a layer of zucchini over top.
Thoroughly, but gently, mix all ingredients together. Cover and
chill.
When ready to serve, mix salad again.
Serves about 6.

title: sticky cinnamon buns
directions: Sprinkle nuts in bottom of a greased 9 X 12 baking dish. Pour pudding over the nuts. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Place rolls on top of this. Mix margarine & sugar and pour over top of rolls. Place in cold oven overnight. Bake next morning at 350 for 20 - 25 minutes. Turn out of pan upside down.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix flour, cheese and seasonings together in pie tin.
Dip potato strips in margarine; coat with flour mixture and arrange on cookie sheet containing 5 tablespoons of melted margarine.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Turn potatoes and cook for another 20 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice, water and salt to boil.
Cover and cook until done.
While rice is steaming, mix 2 eggs, sugar and vanilla. Also cornstarch and evaporated milk.
When rice is done, add 1 quart milk to rice.
Bring to boil again, stirring constantly as it tends to scorch.
When it has come to boil, add second mixture. Pour into casserole and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: chicken casserole (1)
directions: Mix stuffing according to directions. Then add soups, eggs and chicken. Put in greased 13 x 9 pan.
Combine corn flakes and butter and spread out on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar with electric mixer.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add with sour milk; add zucchini.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: yogurt and fruit pops
directions: Note:
Any flavor gelatin and yogurt may be used.

title: club soda pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together and then ladle some on a hot waffle iron.
You can not store this batter, so make only as much as you will use at one time or cook extra waffles and freeze for later use. You can use this same recipe to make yummy pancakes too.

title: chicken salad surprise sandwiches
directions: Spread chicken salad on bread.
Top each with 2 tomato slices and slices of cheese.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes.
Garnish with green peppers.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In a small bowl mix at low speed the powdered sugar, butter, Crisco and milk.
Beat in vanilla and almond extract at medium speed.
Beat until light and fluffy.
If desired, add food coloring.

title: beery beef stew
directions: Coat the cubed meat in the flour which has been mixed with salt, pepper and beef bouillon; set aside.
In a large pot, heat 1/4 cup of olive oil and saute the onion and garlic until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove onion from the pot; add the remaining oil, heat and add the floured meat, browning it well on all sides. Return the onion-garlic mixture along with the beer, the three sauces and herbs.
Mix well; bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers and combine with pectin, sugar, vinegar and lemon juice.
Boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Strain into another pan and boil for one minute.
Add food coloring if you desire.
Remove from heat and put in jars; seal.
Delicious with cream cheese and crackers.

title: pan enchiladas
directions: Heat together enchilada sauce with tomato sauce.
Layer as follows in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: christmas roll
directions: Roll vanilla wafers until crushed fine.
Mix wafer crumbs with all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Use small amount more of condensed milk, if needed.
Roll into two long rolls.
Wrap and chill.
Cut into small slices to serve.

title: canned vegetable soup
directions: Core and boil tomatoes.
Strain to make juice enough for 1 gallon; set aside.
Cook all vegetables together; add enough water to cover.
Cook until vegetables begin to change color; drain. Fill each jar about 3/4 full.
Finish filling each jar with tomato juice.
Add salt.
Put filled jars in pressure canner; bring canner to 10 pounds pressure.
Allow to cook for 25 minutes. Makes 14 quarts.

title: truffles
directions: In double boiler, or microwave, melt 1 cup (6 ounces) chocolate chips with butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Line cookie sheets with foil or waxed paper.
Roll mixture into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Chill until firm. Melt remaining 1 cup chocolate chips and use to dip and coat each completely.
Put back on waxed paper to set by chilling in refrigerator.
Can decorate with white chocolate by melting and drizzling over each individual truffle.

title: ramsey fruit slush punch
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly. Mix with preferred carbonated drink (Ginger Ale is best choice). Makes 3 gallons. Use for holiday punch and top with frozen jello mold ring of fruit afloat in punch.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add Mountain Dew and juice drained from pineapple.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Cook pudding according to package instructions.
Cool.
Mix gelatin, lemon pudding and whipped cream, beating together.
Add drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into large bowl and chill.

title: swiss cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Blend well.
Put mix in a glass pie plate or pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle a few almonds on top.
Serve with crackers or bagel chips.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Mix eggs with milk.
Combine all ingredients and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef, onion, pepper and mushrooms until meat browns. Add garlic salt and herb pepper.
Add mushroom soup and bouillon cube.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add sour cream and sherry to beef mixture.
Combine noodles and beef mixture.
May be placed in a casserole at 200° to keep warm.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all together; bake at 350° in greased loaf pan.

title: green tomato catsup
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer about 20 minutes.
Place in hot, scalded jars.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine washed spinach leaves and strawberries in a large salad bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients until thick.
Pour dressing over salad before serving and toss well.
Very good.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place berries in baked and cooled pie crust.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt, syrup and water in pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in jello and a few drops of red food coloring (optional).
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into balls and place on a non-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Spread half of broccoli in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread half of soup over broccoli.
Repeat remaining broccoli and cheese as before.
Top with bread crumbs and 2 or 3 pats of butter.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons water; add 1 cup boiling water, lemon juice, pineapple and sugar.
Let set in freezer 15 minutes.
Break cake in small pieces.
Put half of cake in bottom of large dish.
Whip 2 envelopes of Dream Whip, fold in gelatin mixture, pour over cake pieces.
Put other half of cake over this. Press down lightly.
Whip 2 envelopes Dream Whip and spread on top of cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top of this.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine over hot water.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna rounds
directions: Mix thoroughly; spread mixture on slices of small rounds of rye bread.
Trim each with pimento-stuffed green olives, sliced. Makes about 36 open faced tea sandwiches.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix well the eggs, milk, butter and vanilla; set aside.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add to egg mixture, then add coconut.
Grease 2 (8-inch) pie pans; divide filling between them.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tasha's favorite biscuits
directions: Mix together well.
Roll out using a little flour to keep from sticking.
Melt butter in pan.
After putting biscuits in pan, pour more melted butter over the top.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Add buttermilk (alternate)
with
flour and remaining ingredients. Flour and grease 1 loaf pan well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool cake 5 minutes, then glaze.

title: impossible pie
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients in blender except coconut.
This makes a large pie (8-inches or a little more).
Let set for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Fry hamburg with onion.
Add all other ingredients except oil. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add oil, if desired.
Cool some, then put in blender until right consistency.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Boil Karo syrup and pecans until a thread forms.
Remove from fire, add the soda and beat until soda is mixed.
Add pecans and spread on a buttered tin.
Break up when cooled.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine sugar, coconut and condensed milk in large bowl.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Refrigerate covered for about 2 to 3 hours or until firm enough to shape into balls.
Line a large baking sheet with wax paper.
Roll the coconut mixture into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
This will make about 3 1/2 dozen bonbons.
Refrigerate until firm.
Melt coating and dip bonbons into mixture, coating well.
Place on wax paper until set. Decorate as desired.

title: eggplant antipasto
directions: Chop the eggplant, green pepper, onion, celery and garlic and saute in oil.
Cook until soft and then add the tomato paste, stuffed olives, wine vinegar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix well and serve hot or cold with any kind of chips or crackers you desire.
Serves 10.

title: wedding cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs.
Add flour, milk and flavoring.
This cake can be baked as a layer cake or sheet cake. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Place one half of potatoes in casserole dish.
Dot each layer with margarine.
Sprinkle each layer with salt. Combine soup, milk, ham, onion, pepper.
Pour one half mixture over potatoes.
Add other half of potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender and slightly brown.

title: goldfish party mix
directions: Mix together; let sit 2 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat well. Stir in cream and add flour. Stir in vanilla. Pour into well greased floured tube or bundt pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: crackling bread
directions: Sift cornmeal, salt and soda together.
Add milk and stir in cracklings.
Form into oblong cakes and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 3 to 4 servings.

title: escalloped eggplant
directions: Peel, slice and boil eggplant until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish about 1 1/2-inches deep.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mock chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Put into 13 x 9 dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool before serving.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom of pan; set aside.
Mix cake according to package directions; pour over nuts and coconut.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Drop by spoonfuls over cake.
Do
not let cheese mixture touch side of pan; it will burn! Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: banana pudding (or pineapple)
directions: Start with vanilla wafers in bowl.
Spread thin slices of bananas over and repeat until all are used, ending with wafers.

title: oyster and artichoke soup
directions: Saute onions, celery and garlic in butter.
Add flour to sauteed vegetables and cook for 5 minutes.
Add water and seasonings.
Add chicken broth, artichokes and liquid; heat for 10 minutes.
Add oysters and liquid and heat for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve when oysters are plump.

title: jan's london broil
directions: Combine dressings and soy sauce well.
Place meat in sauce; cover well and refrigerate overnight.
Place meat on broiler pan and cook to desired doneness.
Slice into thin pieces and serve. Goes well with rice.

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Peel and cook zucchini in 1-inch of water with 1 teaspoon salt for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain.
Then add all the other ingredients. Put in a casserole dish; top with 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken, water, vegetables (except peas), bouillon cubes and pepper in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and discard skin and bones.
Pour remaining ingredients through a sieve, reserving vegetables and broth.
Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Blend in flour until smooth. Stir in reserved liquid with a wire whisk and stir constantly until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Add peas. Taste for salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into a buttered casserole. Top with cheese biscuit crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until liquid is bubbly and biscuits are brown.

title: rum cashews
directions: Combine sugar and rum in medium size saucepan.
Bring to boil; cook 3 minutes or 234° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat. Immediately add cashews and stir to coat.
Return to medium heat and stir constantly to re-melt sugar.
When sugar is golden brown, remove from heat and stir in butter.
Spread on well oiled cookie sheet to dry.
Break apart with fork.

title: easy mustard breadsticks
directions: Unroll and twist dough according to package directions.
Place twists on an ungreased baking sheet.
Combine margarine, mustard and beer in a small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until margarine melts and mixture is smooth.
Brush mustard mixture over twists; sprinkle each with 1/2 teaspoon Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 13 minutes or until golden.
Yield:
10 breadsticks (90 calories each).

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Mix together cheeses, eggs, salt, pepper and garlic.
Place 1/2 jar spaghetti sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture and place in dish. Pour remaining sauce over shells and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: kaiserschmarren(austrian puff pancake)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Mix the flour with the milk.
Add a pinch of salt and 4 eggs yolks (reserve the whites).
Melt the butter in a skillet and add to the flour-milk mixture.
Mix well. Pour the mixture into the skillet.
Beat the egg whites with the sugar.
Fold this into the batter.
Sprinkle raisins on top.
Put skillet in oven and bake for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cut into pie-shaped pieces and serve with a fruit compote.

title: pilgrim pumpkin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly grease and flour a 9 inch square pan. Beat together eggs, sugars, oil and pumpkin. In a separate bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nutmeg. Add to egg mixture. Stir well. Mix in raisins/chocolate chips and nuts. Pour in pan. Bake 34 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Spread with frosting. Cut into 1 by 3 inch bars. Refrigerate. Makes 27 bars.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together soft margarine and peanut butter.
Add both sugars and mix well.
Then add egg and vanilla.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Shape dough into small balls (walnut size) and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and press one Hershey Kiss on each cookie, pressing so cookie cracks around edge.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes until cookie is done.

title: the big easy breakfast
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet over medium heat until lightly browned.
Remove from skillet with slotted spoon.
Add oil; heat over medium-high heat.
Add potatoes and peppers.
Cover; cook 8 to 10 minutes or to desired crispness.
Stir in sausage.
Remove from heat; top with process cheese spread.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon of salt to boiling.
Add pepper and cook for 5 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients; stuff peppers.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: sally's peach or apricot cobbler
directions: Wash fruit, peel and slice peaches.
Apricots do not need to be peeled, just sliced.

Mix together sugar and tapioca to blend and place over sliced fruit that has been placed in a large bowl. Allow to stand about 5 minutes for sugar mixture to blend well. Place fruit in baking pans (large or small) and may be frozen at this stage (covered well with foil of course and sprinkled with a bit fresh to prevent discoloration) or if you wish to bake at this time, cover with prepared pastry, slit pastry several times and bake at 400° for about 40 to 50 minutes, watching carefully not to overbrown.
Since all ovens are different it is a good idea to lower temperature if the pastry crust is getting too dark.
Fruit should be bubbling and crust golden brown when ready.
Serve warm or cold with low-fat ice milk ice cream.

title: brownie chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Prepare brownies as package directs for chewy brownies. Spread evenly in prepared pan. Bake 35 minutes or until set.

title: milk chocolate popcorn
directions: In a large, greased roasting pan, combine popcorn and nuts. In a large, heavy saucepan, combine chocolate chips, corn syrup and butter.
Stir over medium heat until boiling.
Pour over popcorn.
Toss to coat well.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Cool completely.
Store in an airtight container for up to 2 weeks.
Makes about 14 cups.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Combine croutons and cheese.
Place in greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Combine slightly beaten eggs with milk, salt, mustard, onion powder and pepper; mix until blended.
Pour over croutons; crumble bacon over top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until eggs are set.
Garnish with bacon curls. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup, cinnamon, salt, ginger and cloves.
Mix well.
Stir in pumpkin and milk; mix well again.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 300° or until knife will come out clean when sliced through pie.

title: new year's cheese ball
directions: Mix pineapple and softened cream cheese.
Add pepper, onion, 1 cup nuts and salt.
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours and form in ball; roll in remaining 1 cup pecans.
Serve with various snack crackers.

title: quick and easy fish sticks
directions: Cut fish into serving size pieces.
Dip into milk and roll in shake mix.
Fry fish in hot oil for 4 to 5 minutes.
Test fish with a fork.
The flesh is cooked when it flakes apart.
Drain on paper towel.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Melt margarine; remove from heat.
Add mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on sliced party rolls. Add small slice of cheese and small slice of ham to each roll. Wrap in foil and place in a warm oven before eating.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add, alternating with milk and vanilla.
Blend; roll and cut.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put flour in large bowl.
In center of flour, mix salt and margarine and 1 1/2 cups broth.
Mix well until dough is not sticky.
Turn out on floured board, knead and roll out.
Cut dough in strips.
Bring remaining broth to boil.
Drop dumplings by pieces into the boiling broth.
Cook uncovered over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste, cover and cook for another 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Meanwhile, brown meat in butter.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In bowl, combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and noodles.

title: white fudge
directions: Stir in powdered sugar gradually, to mixture of oleo, sugar and milk, which has been brought to a boil and removed from heat. Have extra box of sugar, may need for right consistency.
Nuts and coconut may be added, if desired.
If used, add before adding any extra sugar.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Place zucchini in colander.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt; set aside for 30 minutes.
Squeeze as much liquid as possible from zucchini with your hands; reserve.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until brown.
Add seasonings and soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese.
Cook slowly until cheese melts.
Stir in rice.
Cool.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise. Remove seeds.
Cook in boiling water 3 minutes.
Drain and cool. Place peppers on baking sheet or shallow pan.
Stuff with rice mixture.

title: koblihy(doughnuts)
directions: Dissolve
yeast
with
a small amount warm water.
Then add sugar,
shortening,
salt,
milk
and
one
cup flour and whiskey. Cream
together
and
slowly
add flour one cup at a time to make a soft dough and work the batter like you do for kolaches. Cover
and
let
rise about 45 minutes to one hour. Roll
the dough
out
with
rolling pin and cut circle with a glass.
Then fill
each
circle
with
prunes
or
poppy seed filling.
Pinch the
circle
close
and
place
doughnut on a warmed
flour
cloth and let rise for about 30 minutes.
Turn them
over again, let rise to expand.
Uncover after 3 minutes and
start frying in deep container.
After brown on each side lift
with
wired
spatula and place on absorbent paper. Then roll doughnut in granulated sugar lightly.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Melt butter in frypan. Saute eggplant 5 minutes until slightly soft. Add 1/2 cup hot water, beef stock and seasoning.
Pour over eggplant. Spoon eggplant mixture into a greased, flat baking dish. Combine sour cream, onion flakes, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: taylor's bonbons
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter; add milk, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Make into balls and wrap candy Kisses.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: mac sausage and cheese casserole
directions: While cooking macaroni, simmer soup, milk and hot sauce in a medium saucepan stirring often.
When smooth, add 1/2 cup shredded cheese to sauce and stir in.
Drain macaroni but do not rinse and place them in casserole dish.
Mix in 1/2 of sausage slices.
Pour and mix in cheese sauce.
Top with remainder of sausage slices and sprinkle with remaining cup of shredded cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and walnuts.
Chill in your favorite mold.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook cabbage in boiling water (salted) 10 minutes; drain well.
Place in baking dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch). Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted. Pour over cabbage.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bread crumbs turn golden brown.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Mix cake mix as instructed on box.

title: buffet rye slices
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on party rye slices.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: french potato salad
directions: Toss all ingredients lightly.
If made ahead, you can use dried parsley and reheat in microwave.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Combine oil, sugar, vinegar and salt; pour over first mixture.
Let set in refrigerator for 5 to 9 hours.

title: golden bake chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Skin chicken breasts. Place chicken in ungreased baking pan.
Spread 1 teaspoon of margarine on each piece.
Sprinkle with onions, paprika, garlic salt and pepper. Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes. Garnish with parsley.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Over low heat, melt and mix peanut butter and butterscotch morsels.
Once smooth, mix in Rice Krispies until very well coated.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: chocolate and peanut butter truffles
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter chips in sauce pan over very low heat.
Add cocoa; stir unit smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk; stir constantly until mixture is thick and glossy, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs, and milk. Add frosting to batter mixture. Then add nuts, mix until well blended. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour. Test for doneness.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Make a double boiler by putting a medium pan in a large pan. Put water in bottom pan until it touches the top pan.
Break up the candy bars into 1-2 inch pieces.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix as for corn bread; pour into pint jar.
Push stick into wieners and dip into mixture; let drip, then cook in deep fat until golden brown.

title: round-up supper
directions: Cook hamburger, onion, pepper and celery until done.
Add tomatoes and dry ingredients; mix well.
Now, add the cooked pintos and simmer approximately 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: strawberry angel food
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
Dissolve Jell-O and 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries and sugar and cool in refrigerator until slightly thick.
Whip cream until thick and fold into strawberry mixture.
Cover bottom of pan with cake pieces and spread half of strawberry mixture over.
Repeat with rest of cake and top with mixture.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together except the dried beef. Mix thoroughly.
Then place the minced dried beef in the center of the mixture.
Then lightly pat beef to cover the outside and form a ball.

title: coffee glazed ham steak
directions: Twenty-five minutes before serving, in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, heat corn syrup with instant coffee until coffee is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Slash edges of ham to prevent curling.
Add ham.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes turning once, occasionally spooning syrup mixture over steak.
Place ham on warm plate and spoon mixture over it.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut into strips, 2 x 1/4-inch.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook meat in oil, turning frequently, until brown. Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes for round steak, 5 to 8 for sirloin.
Add green pepper strips during last 5 minutes of simmering.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce; stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cut tomatoes into eighths; place on meat mixture.
Cover; cook on low just until tomatoes are heated through, about 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: jello punch
directions: Boil water and stir in gelatin and sugar until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into milk or plastic cartons or Tupperware containers and freeze.
Mixture should be taken out of freezer so that it is slushy at serving time.
Mix in possibly two bottles ginger ale, depending on personal preference.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream both sugars and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, Rice Krispies, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chips, candy and nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 6 minutes at 375°.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on round 13 to 14-inch pizza pan for crust.
Bake and cool.
Whip together cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on crust.
Top with any choice of fruit cut in half on top of cream.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Put 1 can shrimp in with other ingredients and form into a ball.
Decorate with other can of shrimp.
Garnish with parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: graham cracker fruitcake
directions: Roll out graham crackers
until they are fine.
(Do not throw graham cracker box away!!)
Chop selected nuts very fine.
Melt marshmallows and Eagle Brand milk over low heat.
Mix all other ingredients in big dishpan or something.
Stir in marshmallows and milk.
You may have to mix it with your hands.
Line the graham cracker box with wax paper or Saran Wrap.
Pack the mixed ingredients in the box.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli into a 1-quart buttered casserole. Arrange chicken pieces over broccoli.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Spread crumbs over entire top.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Beat eggs until light, then beat in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add nuts and slightly cooled chocolate mix.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, until top is crusty and filling is set, but soft inside.
Do not overbake!!

title: papaw bill's homemade biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Measure flour into bowl (by spooning into measuring cup and leveling off).
Cut in shortening until like coarse crumbs.
Blend in just enough milk with fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
(Too much milk makes dough too sticky to handle, not enough milk makes biscuits dry.)
Knead gently on lightly floured surface 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut without twisting cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet (1 inch apart for crusty biscuits; almost touching for soft sides) at 500° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve at once.
Makes about 12 delicious 2-inch biscuits.

title: seafood dressing
directions: Cut sausage in normal slices, then quarter and fry.
Remove sausage from pan.
Saute 1/2 onions, peppers and celery in at least 2 sticks margarine.
When vegetables begin to change color, add the other half of diced vegetables, at least 1 more stick margarine, mushrooms and the spices and garlic.
Mix in pieces of sausage.

title: country pork ribs (boneless or boned)
directions: Cook at 350° for 2 hours. Turn oven off and cool in oven.

title: five layer cake
directions: Mix flour, pecans, sugar and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Spread 1 cup Cool Whip on cream cheese mixture.
Mix pudding with milk.
Pour over Cool Whip and refrigerate 1 hour.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: microwave beef stroganoff
directions: Combine butter, onion and garlic in 2-quart casserole dish. Cook, covered, on full power for 2 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until onion is tender.
Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut meat into thin bite-size strips.
Add meat to casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power for 3 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Continue cooking, covered, for 10 to 13 minutes, or until meat is cooked. Stir in soup, mushrooms and catsup.
Heat, covered, on full power for 1 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until heated through.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat, covered, on full power for 1 to 2 1/2 minutes, or until sour cream is heated through.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry chicken breasts
directions: Mix marinade, pour over chicken breasts.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix sugar, salt and vinegar in blender for 2 minutes. Add oil and blend well. Add celery seed, mustard seed and onion.
May be stored in refrigerator for future use.

title: scottsdale potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 7 x 10-inch pan. Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl and season with salt and pepper.
Pour into a baking dish.
Mix cornflake crumbs and 1/2 cup butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake about 45 minutes, until browned.

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake in moderate oven until firm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and set aside.
Bring water to a boil in a large pan; add rice and soup mix.
Cook until the rice is tender.
Add hamburger and all the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in 2 or 3 greased pans and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake one and cover two with foil; put in freezer for later, if you like.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs before baking.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix coconut and milk and freeze.
Once firm, roll into balls and refreeze.
Dip into chocolate quickly.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Place frozen hash browns in large casserole.
Mix the rest of ingredients in bowl and pour over hash browns.
Mix to coat all potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° to 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Very tasty.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat well.
Quickly pour into greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Enjoy!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add water and butter.
Cook until thick over medium heat or in double boiler.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot over ice cream or cake or both!

title: betty's butter pecan ice cream
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in oven. Add pecans and roast at 300° for about 20 minutes, stirring 2 times. Set aside until needed. Scald milk. Beat eggs. Add sugar and salt. Add egg mixture to milk and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add half and half or cream, vanilla flavoring and butter flavoring. Let cool. When ready to freeze, pour into freezer and add enough milk to reach fill line. Add roasted pecans. Makes 1 gallon.

title: dip for fresh fruits(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Keep refrigerated until ready to use. Can be frozen if not used right away.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrot in margarine for 10 minutes. Add flour to sauteed mixture, stirring well; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Combine broth and half and half. Gradually stir in broth mixture; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in salt and pepper. Add chicken, stirring well. Pour chicken mixture into a shallow 2-quart casserole. Top with pastry; cut slits to allow steam to escape. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: chicken casserole 1
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into casserole. Store covered in the refrigerator overnight. Set out 1 hour and then bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese vegetable chowder
directions: In Dutch oven or large saucepan, melt margarine; add cabbage, onions, celery, carrots and peas.
Saute for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add corn, milk, salt, pepper and thyme. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally; add cheese and stir until melted.
Makes six 1 1/3 cup servings.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Scoop ice cream into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Serve immediately or place in shallow pan, cover and store in freezer.

title: buckeyes
directions: Beat egg well.
Add salt, 1 cup confectioners sugar, vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Mix well; then add remaining cup of sugar.

title: sugar cookies(my norwegian grandmother's recipe)
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add oil. Mix in dry ingredients.
Refrigerate at least one hour or more is better.
Drop by spoonfuls and roll in balls to make perfectly round cookies.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and press down to flatten.
Bake at 400° until brown on edges, 10 to 12 minutes. Makes several dozen.
I half recipe usually.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese, blend in sour cream until well blended; add chilies to mixture.
Spread mixture on tortilla then roll up and refrigerate overnight.
Slice into mouth size pieces and serve with salsa.

title: hot mocha milk(microwave)
directions: Combine chocolate syrup, instant coffee and cinnamon in a heat-resistant, nonmetallic mug or cup.
Stir in milk and heat uncovered on Full power 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until hot (170°). Don't allow milk to boil.
Garnish with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: wet bottom shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and Crisco together.
Reserve 1 cup of crumbs for the top.
Mix the rest with the liquid ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Pour 1-inch of water in 2-quart saucepan.
Pour in chocolate and peanut butter.
Stir constantly to melt and blend.
Remove from heat when melted.
Add corn flakes and mix to coat flakes thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool until firm. Makes about 3 dozen clusters.

title: chocolate chip sour cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Then add sour cream and chocolate chips.

title: iced almonds
directions: Line baking sheet with foil; butter the foil.
In heavy 8-inch skillet, combine nuts, sugar and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly 9 minutes or until sugar melts and turns a rich brown color.
Remove from heat.
Spread mixture onto prepared baking sheet.
Cool completely.
Break into clusters. Store tightly covered.

title: dora potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Drain meat.
Chop up onion in meat. Peel and slice potatoes.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir.
Cook on low heat or bake in oven until potatoes are tender.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: kyra's hot chocolate
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients.
Heat milk to boiling point. Pour over cocoa mix and stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla and serve at once in warm cups.
Makes 12 servings.

title: ham and green onion cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let chill for 1 hour.

title: louisiana chicken and shrimp chili
directions: Grill chicken breasts and dice into cubes. If shrimp are very large, dice them too. Drain liquid off peppers and dice. Dice bacon and fry it until very crisp in a large soup pot; do not burn it. Add the diced onions and cook until transparent. Take the bacon and onions from the pot with a slotted spoon and set aside. Make a roux by mixing the olive oil and bacon fat and adding flour a little at a time, whisking until the mixture is like wet sand. Whisk chicken broth into flour mixture and stir until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and simmer one half hour, stirring often. Season to taste.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk in a large bowl; let stand 1 hour. Add brown sugar and egg; mix well.
Combine the next 6 ingredients; stir into oat mixture.
Stir in oil, lemon rind and raisins.
Spoon into oiled muffin pans.
Fill half full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen large or 18 medium muffins.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a medium skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add garlic, onion, and green pepper and saute until onions are soft. Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, place ground beef, crushed crackers, cheddar cheese, taco seasoning, sauteed onion and green pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Press beef mixture into a 9x5 inch loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.
Check with a meat thermometer for doneness.
Internal temperature should read 165°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain and cool.
Then stir together with celery, carrots, onion and eggs.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, cornstarch, self-rising flour and water.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add egg yolks. Cook 2 minutes. Add rind of lemon and lemon juice.
Cook 1 minute more and remove from heat.
Add butter and spread.
Enough filling for 3 layer cake.

title: white trash
