directions: Melt chocolate and butter in microwave; watch carefully and stir.
Place dry ingredients in large bowl. Pour white chocolate over dry ingredients; mix well. Pour onto buttered foil until soft.

title: watercress dip
directions: Remove tough stems from watercress.
In food processor with knife blade attached or in blender, blend watercress, mayo, sour cream, Dijon mustard and salt until blended.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Melt oil (or margarine) and peanut butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add sugar to egg in a mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Stir in the peanut butter mixture and vanilla.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients, then peanuts.
Turn into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar into a bowl.
Add egg, sour cream, vanilla, nutmeg and beat to a smooth thin batter.
Blend in apples.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: no-fail pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in medium size bowl.
Add milk, cooking oil and egg; mix with spoon until blended.
Batter will be lumpy.
Put small amount of cooking oil on a paper towel and wipe skillet.
Turn burner on high and heat skillet until a drop of water dances.
Turn fire down to medium.
Pour small amount of batter into skillet.
Cook on medium until bubbles form and pop. Turn and cook until light brown.
Serve hot.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
When it thickens, take off the stove.
Knead the lumps out.

title: delicious easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well except pecans.
Roll into ball, then roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
It is ready to use, with assorted crackers, in an hour or two.
Or, it can be made up a few days ahead of use.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream fat and sugar.
Add egg, then applesauce into which soda has been stirred.
Sift salt and spices into flour.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/4 hours in moderate oven.

title: spaetzle  (german dumplings) and chicken
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients. Beat until batter blisters. Drop in boiling water or broth using butter knife. (Dip butter knife in boiling water every few dumplings to keep from sticking to knife.) Skim as they rise. Place in a container with a little butter.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Place brisket
in a large baking pan.
Pour 2 ounces of liquid smoke
on both sides of meat.
Sprinkle both sides with celery seed,
onion and garlic salt.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.	When
ready
to
bake,	sprinkle both sides with salt, pepper
and
Worcestershire
sauce.
Cover meat by making a tent and press edges tight around pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours. Remove
from
oven	and pour 6 ounces of Woody's sauce over
meat. Recover
and
bake
for
hour
at
275°. Refrigerate overnight.	Slice when cold.

title: soy fried rice
directions: Heat oil. Add eggs, mixing constantly, while breaking up with fork. Add eggs and onions to rice with soy sauce to color rice brown. Blend very well and serve hot.

title: pat's quick dinner rolls
directions: Place eggs in measuring cup.
Beat and add hot tap water to make cups.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Add 3 more cups flour to knead.
Let rise 20 minutes; make into rolls.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 20 to 24.

title: cream cheese lasagna
directions: Cook beef and onion in a heavy skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, water, flakes, Italian seasoning, bouillon and garlic powder. Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Combine the cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and eggs; stir well.
Spoon small amount of meat sauce into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer with half each of noodles, cheese mixture, pepperoni, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers with ingredients. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: quick seafood surprise
directions: Use any amounts desired.
Heat soup.
Saute scallops in minimum amount of butter.
Add all seafood to soup.
Pour over cooked rice.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.

title: stuffed brussels sprouts
directions: Cook sprouts in salted boiling water for 3 minutes.
Cool in cold water.
Drain well.
Beat cream cheese, adding milk.
Add shredded corned beef and horseradish.
Mix well.
Cut a wedge out of each sprout.
Stuff opening with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with salt.
Run a toothpick through each sprout and arrange on platter. Serves 30.

title: peanut butter
directions: Stir the sugar, Karo and water continually to hard boil, then add the peanuts.
Keep stirring to 260°.
Add the oleo and cook to 290°.
Take off heat and add the salt and soda.
Let raise in pan a few seconds.
Pour over buttered foil and stretch to put into shape.

title: fish in beer batter
directions: Combine flour, beer, egg, salt and baking powder in a bowl; beat lightly.
Dip fish into batter to coat well.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Excellent batter with any type of fish.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet.
Drain off fat if necessary.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot over cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: caramel bars
directions: Over low heat, melt caramels with milk.
Stir until smooth. Stir in walnuts; set aside.
Mix well (like pie crust) the butter, brown sugar, salt, flour, baking soda and oatmeal.
Spread 2 1/2 cups of mixture on bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan. Pat down firmly with large spoon.
Spread caramel mixture on top. Sprinkle rest of crust on top of filling; pat gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw frozen spinach (room temperature). Drain and squeeze out all water. Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate before serving. Serve with crackers or rye bread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: roast beef, carrots, potatoes
directions: Put 1/2 cup grease in a large fryer.
Roll roast in flour; put in fryer.
Cover with lid.
Cook medium until brown.
In a big boiler, brown 1 cup flour; pour water in boiler and put roast in gravy.
Add carrots, potatoes and chopped onion.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender.

title: baked beans
directions: Cooking raw rice has long been a "thorn in the side" of many a good cook.
Try this "lazy rice" recipe for Steamed Rice.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter, sugars and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheets onto wire racks to cool completely.

title: penne with turkey sausage
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in large skillet.
Saute garlic over medium heat until golden and crisp 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove garlic and set aside.

title: pecan bars
directions: Pour over hot crust; bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Center should be almost firm.

title: strawberry shortcake salad
directions: Make Jell-O with 3 cups hot water.
Add to Jell-O the strawberries.
Mix cake cubes with Jell-O and strawberries.
Just before serving fold in whipped topping.

title: tequila pork roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sliced clove of garlic. Pour marinade ingredients together. Cut slits in pork roast and insert garlic slivers into the slits. Pour marinade and roast in a resealable bag and marinate at least 8 hours. You can grill or bake until done. Takes approximately 1 1/2 hrs. at 350°.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream the butter, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Leave 1-inch of space around the edge.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with chocolate chips while still hot.
Leave for about 5 minutes.
When the chips are melted, spread evenly.

title: buckeye balls
directions: 1. In large bowl mix peanut butter, butter, vanilla extract and powdered sugar ingredients by hand until dough is smooth.

title: baked apple donuts
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and sugar. Cut in shortening until mixture is fine.
Mix together egg, milk and apple and add to flour mixture.
Mix quickly but thoroughly. Fill greased muffin pans (small size) 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May be dipped in butter, then rolled in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon (1/3 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon).

title: tomato-cucumber mayonnaise dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, blending thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Great for green salads, meat and seafood salads.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Begin with lettuce.
Layer each ingredient in large salad bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream and spread over top. Sprinkle with cheese and chill 12 hours before serving.
Recipe can be halved for smaller salad.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla, salad oil, sugar, plain flour, soda, salt and cinnamon, then add 4 cups sliced apples and chopped nuts. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let cake cool, then frost or eat plain.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan. Make 3 holes with spoon.
Put vanilla in one, melted margarine in one and vinegar in last hole.
Pour water over all and mix well. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting or canned frosting.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and beat 6 minutes.
Add poppy seeds. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot peppers and franks
directions: Wash peppers, remove seeds.
Slice round (using rubber gloves).
Slice wieners into chunks.
In large kettle, combine catsup, vinegar, sugar, salt and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Add peppers and wieners; return to boiling again Cook for 10 minutes. Pack into hot jars.
Process in hot water bath for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: smothered chops
directions: Place chops in covered skillet.
Top with lemon slices, onion, green pepper rings and salt.
Pour tomato juice over all.
Simmer until done.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes and tossed salad. Makes 6 servings.

title: jim wentworth's southern pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda, salt and buttermilk in a saucepan. Bring to a boil,
stirring
constantly.
Add
oleo and pecans; lower heat
slightly and continue stirring until candy forms a hard ball in
cold
water.
This
will take a good while.
You will know you are
close
when the candy begins to turn brown from the
pecans and
sugar
cooking down.
Remove from heat; cool
slightly, beating constantly.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper to harden.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with brown sugar.
Beat milk, 2 tablespoons brown sugar, salt, fat and whole wheat flour.
Add enough white flour to make a satiny dough.
Cover with wax paper and thin towel; let double in bulk.
Knead down; let rise again and put in loaves (2 loaves).
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
By adding 1 egg, more brown sugar, raisins and cinnamon or dates, you can change this into a very delicious quick bread.
Also can be iced.

title: hot sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Remove sausage from casings.
Cook in large skillet.
Break up meat with fork until no longer pink.
Drain fat.
Spoon sausage into large bowl; cool completely.
Add cheese, biscuit mix and water with a fork until blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on large cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and brown.

title: mama mary's raspberry slush
directions: Combine pineapple juice, raspberries, lemonade, lemon juice, sugar and punch mix.
Add water to make 2 gallons; blend thoroughly.
Freeze 24 hours or longer.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving. Chop through mixture; spoon into serving glasses, 2/3 full.
Add lemon-lime carbonated beverage to fill. Garnish with whole berries and mint sprigs.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with apple slices.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with margarine.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread on top of crust. Re-freeze.
Mix sugar, evaporated milk, vanilla, chocolate and margarine.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour over ice cream and re-freeze.
Mix Cool Whip with nuts and spread over chocolate. Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: mrs. barr's rhubarb jam
directions: Bring to boil the rhubarb, sugar and pineapple with juice in large kettle.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, or until rhubarb is tender.
Remove from the heat and stir in the jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars.
Seal and store in the refrigerator.
Makes 3 pints.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into prepared loaf pan. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked fudge pudding
directions: Combine flour, 3/4 cup brown sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder, salt and spices in mixing bowl. Stir in milk, melted butter and vanilla extract. Add nuts. Spoon into ungreased 8-inch square pan. Combine remaining 1 1/4 cups brown sugar with remaining 1/4 cup cocoa. Sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries with water until they pop.
While hot, add 2 packages red Jell-O, 2 cups sugar and let cool, then add 1 cup pecans and 1 cup drained pineapple.

title: shrimp and linguine alfredo
directions: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken into Pam sprayed 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix soup and broth together.
Pour half of mixture over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with remaining broth and soup.
Pour on top of chicken mixture.
Melt butter; pour on top of stuffing.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stir-fried broccoli and mushrooms
directions: In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Stir-fry for 5 minutes or until tender and crisp.

title: ben's mud
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter and microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir and microwave for another 1/2 minute or until all has melted and is smooth.
Add vanilla.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Wash and slice eggplant.
Put in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and rinse with cold water to clean.
Squeeze out excess water.
Dip eggplant in egg, then in flour.
Lightly fry until golden.
In casserole baking dish (approximately 11 x 14 x 3-inches), place a layer of eggplant to cover bottom.
Sprinkle some Mozzarella, grated eggs, Romano cheese and spices.
Repeat this layering process until all eggplant is used.
Mix 1/2 cup water and 1/4 cup olive oil.
Sprinkle this mixture on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini cheese casserole
directions: Bring 1 inch of water to boil; add zucchini.
Salt.
Cover and cook until tender.
Drain zucchini; put in greased casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients and spread over zucchini.
Broil until cheese melts and begins to brown.

title: peppy seafood sauce
directions: Combine and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: baked fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit and arrange in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Combine brown sugar, margarine and ginger over low heat until margarine is melted.
Pour over fruit and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Blend the oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift the flour with the salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to the egg mixture with buttermilk; blend well.
Add dates, cranberries, nuts and rind.
Stir to blend.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350° in tube pan.

title: never fail beef dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place roast in roasting pan. Evenly sprinkle soup mix over meat. Spoon mushroom soup over mix and meat and spread soup to completely cover top of meat. DO NOT ADD WATER. Arrange potatoes and carrots around meat. Cover and roast in preheated oven about 3 hours.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar, salt, baking powder and Crisco; mix well.
Put egg in cup; mix well.
Add vinegar.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Add to flour mixture; mix.
Roll dough; cut into squares large enough to roll around apple.

title: sawdust cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls (size of walnuts).
Flatten with glass bottom dipped in white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take juice from pineapple chunks and pour over bananas.
Let soak for 30 minutes.
Drain banana slices; mix with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all together and pour into baking dish.

title: hawaiian bread dill dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and refrigerate.
When ready to use, place the Hawaiian bread on a large plate and break the bread apart in the center, large enough for your dip.
Lay the broken pieces around the bread.
Pull the bread apart and dip.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 5 tablespoons melted margarine and butter.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish and press down.

title: cream mushroom dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Serve as a dip with chips, crackers, fresh fruit or vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add just a little vinegar, then oil. Repeat with vinegar.
Use a mixer to add ingredients.
Great with watermelon, cantaloupe, honeydew and other fruit.

title: polly wants a cracker
directions: Butter a large cookie sheet and place graham crackers, side by side, to fit pan, breaking some if needed to fit pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over crackers.
Mix sugar and oleo in saucepan; cook until sugar dissolves.
Spoon evenly over crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Will be crispy when done.
Kids love these, may be broken into any size.

title: smoked trout dip a'la mk
directions: Put half of trout in food processor.
Pulse until fine.
Cut remaining trout into bite size chunks.
Pour trout into large bowl.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers, chips, bagels or on small biscuits.

title: sundae dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze for 15 minutes.
Spread softened ice cream over crumb crust.
Freeze 15 minutes.
Combine milk, 1/2 cup margarine, sugar and unsweetened chocolate in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce to low and cook for 20 minutes or until thick.
Cool to room temperature. Pour over ice cream and freeze.
Top with whipped topping.
Freeze until hard.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and spread in bottom of long or round tray.
Top with peppers, onions, tomatoes and taco/picante/salsa, your choice.
Dip your chips in.

title: chicken stew
directions: Skin and wash chicken pieces.
Dry with paper towel.
In large pan, brown chicken in hot oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Remove chicken from pan.
Add chopped onion, green pepper, crushed garlic and curry powder.
Cook over low heat until onion is tender.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients, except almonds. Cook 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle with almonds. Serve over steamed rice.

title: pralines(mexican candy)
directions: Butter sides of heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Stir sugar, vanilla and sour cream together in the saucepan.
Continue to stir until all melts and then cook to soft ball stage (236° on a candy thermometer).
Add vanilla; beat until mixture thickens.
Add the pecan halves and stir until all are coated.
Turn out on greased platter.
Separate the nuts after they cool.

title: mexican macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; set aside.
Brown sausage, onion and green pepper until sausage is done; drain well.
Combine sausage mixture with remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2 quart casserole; sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: french apple pie
directions: Quarter and slice apples.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Toss with the apples and put into crust.

title: plain cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients, then add enough milk to make gravy-like and add vanilla flavoring last.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Any vegetables may be used!
Heat oil in skillet until very hot.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add celery, zucchini, and carrots and stir 1 minute.
Add chicken broth.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add peas; cover and cook 30 seconds.
Season; stir and serve with soy sauce.
Serves 6.

title: poor man's rice pudding
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Add sugar, Crisco, salt and nutmeg. Stir into milk.
Pour into baking dish and bake in slow oven at 275° for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally during the first 1 hour of cooking.

title: chinese noodle haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch bits and peanut butter together over low heat.
Then add Chinese noodles.
Stir in good and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper to cool.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: In an 8-inch square pan, mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in oats and pack firmly in pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: coffee can stuff
directions: Mix cereals, pretzels, Spanish peanuts and mixed nuts together; put in 2 large roasters.
Melt butter, margarine, oil and Worcestershire sauce together.
Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake in slow oven at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir often and sprinkle with garlic salt every time you stir.
When cool, store in ice cream pails or coffee cans.
Keep in cool place.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in crushed pineapple with juice.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and nutmeg and stir into mix.
Mix in nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour. Drop rounded teaspoon about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until, when touched lightly with finger, no imprint remains.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen.

title: mother's strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, cornstarch, sugar and salt until thick. Remove from heat and add Jell-O. Cool and pour over strawberries in a baked pie crust. Chill.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash grapes and let drain.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar. Add the vanilla and fold in the sour cream.
Fold in your grapes.

title: heavenly fillets
directions: Place fish in a single layer onto a well-greased baking dish. Brush with lemon juice.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts; remove bone and cut into chunks (may use whole chicken if you wish).
Cook broccoli until almost done, drain and cool (blanch and cool fresh broccoli).
Place broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken on top.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, curry, lemon juice and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle top with croutons.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Toss with apples and lemon juice.
Place apples in crust and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and put margarine on top.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in oil.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add beans and heat well.

title: layered cream pastry
directions: Cream together sugar and butter or shortening in large mixing bowl.
Add honey, eggs and milk and mix well.
Work in dry ingredients with hands, kneading well until smooth.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll each part out to fit a 10 x 13-inch cookie sheet with no sides, or inverted cookie sheets.
Bake on ungreased sheets at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Before cooling, run a long knife under it to loosen from pan.
Cool.

title: pumpkin mousse
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg yolks and egg whites.
Mix well and beat in egg yolks vigorously.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour the mixture into a 1-quart oiled baking dish and set dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake the mousse at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve mousse hot, with roast chicken, turkey or duck.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread one package of uncooked, thawed broccoli over the bottom of a rectangular casserole.
Next layer 1/2 of the ingredients, cheese, mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Spread 2nd package of broccoli and layer last 1/2 of ingredients, warm water and butter and add to Stove Top stuffing to moisten.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: amish bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into well-greased and sugared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; test.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: You will need a Pyrex bowl, paper bag and wax paper or cookie sheet.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Chop, mix and chill.
Great for vegetables.

title: onion casserole
directions: In 8
x 12-inch baking dish, line with layer of zucchini, layer
onions,
layer
tomatoes, layer cheese and layer of Ritz crackers.
Drizzle	butter	on
top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Dredge chicken with flour or Baking Magic seasoning mix.
Saute until golden brown in oil.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer the chicken, covered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve with pasta or rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump
all
ingredients	into large bowl and beat for 20 minutes, until smooth.
Dust a greased 10-inch tube pan with a mixture
of
tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon nutmeg.
Dump batter into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green pea salad
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with spinach or lettuce.
Cook peas in boiling water 3 or 4 minutes until slightly cooked.
Take off and drain.
Put peas in ice water for 10 minutes.
Drain. Combine peas, chopped eggs, chopped onions, mayonnaise and sugar in mixing bowl.
Toss well.
Pour over lettuce.
Top with crumbled bacon and Parmesan cheese.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: First Bowl:
Drain pineapple, saving liquid, and mix pineapple with cream cheese.

title: taco dip
directions: In small bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix together.
Chop remaining ingredients.
Place on top of mix by layering each vegetable.
Place grated cheese on top.
Serve with nachos.

title: white cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll out on lightly floured board and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes whole until you can pierce with a fork.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Combine 1/3 cup bacon drippings with next 5 ingredients.
Heat and stir until thickened. Add potatoes, onion and the bacon, crumbled; toss and heat through.
Serves 6.

title: veggie pizza(low-fat appetizer)
directions: Mix veggies (mushrooms, peppers, broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, etc.).
Let cream cheese soften at room temperature. Bake pizza crust (follow directions on package) on cookie sheet. Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, spices and mayo together in a bowl. Spread over crust when cool.
Top with fresh veggies of any kind. Chill overnight and serve.
Yum-yum and good 4 U!

title: lo-cal milkshake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high speed until ice is dispersed and shake is thick.
If peanut butter variation is used, allowance must be made in food plan for the peanut butter.

title: lasagna
directions: Start boiling water when browning hamburger.
Brown hamburger and garlic clove.
After browning, drain off excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce mix, tomato paste and whole tomatoes (chop up whole tomatoes and add all the remaining juice).
Let this mixture simmer for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Boil lasagna noodles until done.
Use large cake pan, place 1 row lasagna noodles; cover with hamburger mixture, 1/3 of cottage cheese and 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese. Begin again for 3 tiers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: play dough
directions: In large saucepan, mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Cook on medium high heat stirring constantly until consistency of play dough is suitable. Once firm, turn dough onto counter.
Let cool and knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: fruit punch
directions: The frozen fruit punch concentrate, water and ginger ale may be mixed together no more than 3 hours before serving.
Add the sherbet prior to serving and beat for a few minutes with a mixer.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Put Crackers in freezer bag and roll with a rolling pin to crush.
Cover Chicken with melted butter.
Roll in bread crumbs. Bake (uncovered) for 45-60 minutes at 350 degrees.
Let stand 4-5 minutes.
(Quick and Easy Preparation.)

title: harvard tea
directions: Put tea bags in boiling water; remove from heat and let set for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix sugar and juices in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Take syrup off fire; add 9 sprigs mint.
Let set for 10 to 15 minutes; lift mint out.
Pour tea and syrup mixture into a gallon jar.
Fill with water.
(Can add more sugar if necessary.)

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well. Stir in oatmeal, raisins, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: cornflake casserole or stuffing
directions: Measure cornflakes into large bowl.
Brown sausage in heavy skillet, breaking it up as it cooks.
When browned, add onion and celery until "crisp" cooked.
Into bowl of cornflakes, add poultry seasoning and toss to combine.
Add entire contents of skillet to flakes.
Toss lightly to combine and add the nuts.
Pour into casserole or stuff turkey.
Bake 30 minutes in casserole or longer in turkey.

title: microwave chicken mexicana
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces; arrange in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave at High for 6 to 8 minutes or until chicken is done.
Cool; cut chicken into smaller pieces, if desired.

title: apple roll
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Place in a baking dish, 13 x 9-inch.
Roll out dough and place sliced apples, cinnamon and dots of butter on it, then roll tight.
Cut in slices.
Place in baking dish with syrup.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Blend all in blender until smooth.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Put all of the ingredients listed in a blender; blend at low to medium speed (whip on some blenders) until smooth.
Pour into an unbaked frozen pie shell.
(Don't forget to prick pie shell with a fork!)
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Allow to cool, then refrigerate for several hours.

title: cajun spice mix
directions: Combine all the spices and mix until well blended.
Store tightly covered in a cool dry location.
(Note:
Four times the amount makes about 1 cup.)

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Wash and cut up fresh strawberries.
Add to thawed frozen strawberries.
Line bottom of cake pan with half of the strawberry mixture.
Place Twinkies over the mixture.
Add the other half of the strawberry mixture on top of the Twinkies.
Top with the Cool Whip.
Garnish with a few sliced strawberries to make it look pretty.
Leave green leaves on the garnished strawberries.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Crumble about 10 or 12 cheese crackers and spread on the bottom of a baking dish.
Drain the asparagus and peas and pour into dish.
Mix the soup (undiluted) and vegetables together. Sprinkle cheese crackers on the top.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until top is turning light brown.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: skoby's corn
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour into an oven-safe casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until tender (don't overcook); drain.
Arrange on greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and sherry and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 25 to 30 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Trim with pimento strips if desired.
Serves six.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add sugar and liquids and beat until smooth.
Add more sugar or cream to make the consistency to spread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook head broccoli on top of stove about 10 minutes.
Drain and put in greased casserole.
Cook sauce on top of stove until cheese melts.
Top broccoli with cheese sauce and crumbs (bread or cracker crumbs).
Bake 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: butter
directions: Put whipping cream in jar (make sure there is space in top of jar or use two).
Now, shake, shake, shake!
Butter is done when there is a lump (this is the butter).
Pour off liquid.
You can add yellow food coloring and salt to taste.
This is great for kids to do at family gatherings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients. Layer peaches in dish. Cover with bread. Pour mixture on top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for five minutes.
Grease and sprinkle the pan with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Place carrots in a casserole. Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish and cooking liquid. Spread over carrots. Sprinkle with cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: While spaghetti is cooking, saute the garlic briefly in the oil.
Add all the other ingredients and simmer until the spaghetti is ready. Drain spaghetti. Toss with the sauce in a bowl and serve immediately. Serves 2 to 4.

title: cathedral cookies
directions: Melt
butter
and chocolate pieces.
Add nuts (chopped) and add
marshmallows.	Mix.
Roll on waxed paper covered with coconut in the shape of rolls.
Makes 3 rolls.
Chill.
Cut in slices.

title: california walnut squares
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together the next 6 ingredients; pour on crust.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top is crusty.
Cool.
Beat together the last 6 ingredients and frost bars.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into balls and drop in hot oil. Drain on paper towels.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Heat
all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour sauce over it.
Bake uncovered in moderate oven (325° to 350°) 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brookwood's beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in covered pan.
Cook at 250° for 5 hours.
No peeking!

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine
first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 cup water, mixing well to make a paste.
Add remaining 1
1/2 cups water, egg yolks and butter; stir well.
Cook over medium heat
(about
minutes)
until
mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour filling into baked pastry shell.

title: good yellow punch
directions: Put Kool-Aid and sugar in 1-gallon jar. Add small amount water, then add juice and ginger ale. Fill with water. Makes 1 gallon.

title: kraut and pork
directions: Cut up pork chops into small pieces and brown in small amount of fat in a large saucepan.
Add kraut.
Cover with water just to top of kraut and add salt.
Cover and simmer at least half day.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Can also use lemon or butterscotch pudding.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter; add sugar continuing to cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well together with each addition. Add 1 1/2 cups of the flour, cocoa, pudding, salt, baking powder, sour cream and milk, continuing beating all the time.
Add the rest of the flour and the vanilla.
Stir in the nuts with a spoon. Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.
Let cake cool in the pan and it will be moist.

title: wild rice and venison
directions: Brown venison in skillet.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook and drain fat from ground beef; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put into a casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: greek butter cookies
directions: Cream butter in bowl for 10 to 15 minutes or until very light. Add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, egg yolks and vanilla; mix well. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Shape dough into small crescents.
Place 1-inch apart on 2 ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Place cookies carefully on waxed paper sprinkled with 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Sprinkle with remaining confectioners sugar.
Cool thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
60 servings.

title: fat-free vege-baked potatoes
directions: Chop broccoli, onion and pepper.
Dice lunch meat.
Combine all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add potatoes and picante sauce.

title: chili
directions: In a large pot, heat oil and add onion, garlic and peppers. Saute until onion is tender and add meats.
Cook through.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauces and beans.
Add remaining ingredients and lower heat to simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.
Serve over elbow macaroni or noodles.

title: dip
directions: Mix sour cream and Ranch dressing; spread in a pie plate. Cover with cheese.
Cover with onions.
Cover with tomatoes. Serve with chips.

title: sour cream walnut cake
directions: Grease two 9-inch round layer pans.
Dust with flour.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder on wax paper. Combine butter, shortening, sugar and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes until light and fluffy.
Beat in orange rind.
Combine sour cream and milk.
Stir flour mixture into batter, alternating with sour cream mix, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in walnuts.
Scrape batter into prepared pans. Bake 30 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Let cool and ice with Butter Rum Frosting.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir in fruit and pour in pie shells.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Can be frozen.
Makes 2 pies.
Food coloring can be added after beating cream cheese, milk and lemon juice.
Have a ball!

title: aggression cookies
directions: Dump all ingredients, except white sugar, into a bowl.
Mash it, smash it, knead it and squeeze it until it is thoroughly mixed. Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet (greased).
Makes 4 to 6 dozen, depending on size of balls.
Butter the bottom of a glass and dip into white sugar.
Mash the balls flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate-orange pecan pie
directions: For crust:
Place flour and salt in large bowl.
Add butter and shortening and rub with fingertips until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Gradually mix in enough water until dough forms moist clumps.
Gather into ball; flatten into disk.
Wrap in plastic; chill 30 minutes.

title: pink lemonade
directions: Mix lemonade, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together, stirring well.
Put in baked pie shell and refrigerate until served.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Remove and spread marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: lace cookies
directions: Blend all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add Crisco, eggs and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
Fold in coconut.
Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten with knife that has been dipped in cold water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: candy canes cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the red food coloring.
Divide the dough in half.
Add the red food coloring to one half of the dough.
Roll approximately 1 teaspoon of each color dough in 4-inch strips.
Twine the two colors together to get candy cane effect.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Curve top down.
Bake 9 minutes at 375°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour with salt and pepper.
Pound into meat.
Brown on both sides in shortening in 12-inch skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, on top of range or bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with gravy in skillet.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ann's blueberry cheese cake
directions: Put blueberry pie filling in fridge.
Soften cream cheese to mix.
Beat 4 egg whites; gradually add 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put yolks in cream cheese and mix.
Blend cream cheese and egg whites together.
Butter an 8-inch spring pan and sprinkle with finely crushed zwieback crackers.
Put mix in pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine corn, sour cream, eggs and salad oil.
Beat well.
Combine cornmeal and baking powder in a separate bowl.
Stir into corn mixture.
Pour into a 10-inch skillet and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: nacho dip
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook until cheese melts, about 1 hour.

title: wanda's broccoli and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and spoon into a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; fold in pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday date bread
directions: Prepare loaf pan by lightly greasing and coating with plain bread crumbs.
Mix chopped dates with water and baking soda; let cool.
Beat eggs; add sugar.
Add date mixture; stir thoroughly. Gradually add flour, baking powder, salt and pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sugar and spice walnuts
directions: Pour oil to depth of one inch in electric skillet.
Heat to 350°.
Bring water to boil in large saucepan.
Add walnuts, return to boil, boil one minute.
Drain walnuts well.
In large bowl, toss walnuts with sugar.
Place half the walnuts in hot oil, and deep fry for five minutes until walnuts are golden.
Remove walnuts with a slotted spoon and place on paper towel to drain.
Deep fry remaining walnuts.
When all walnuts are deep fried, return to large bowl and toss with cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.

title: williette's barbecue sauce
directions: Season meat or chicken to taste with the salt, pepper, m.s.g./Accent, Mrs. Dash and Cavender's Greek seasoning.
Set aside until sauce is mixed.
Preheat oven to 325° to 350° (depends on cooking time for your personal oven).

title: m&m's easy party cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add combined flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup candies and reserve remaining candies for decorating.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto baking sheets.
Press an additional 3 to 4 candies on top of each cookie.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly on baking sheet, then remove to rack to cool.

title: mexican dip
directions: Soften refried beans, cream cheese and sour cream in microwave.
Add taco mix and stir well.
Pour into casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Eat with nacho chips.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots 20 minutes until crisp and tender in boiling saltwater. Cool. Mix remaining ingredients and add carrots. Serve cold.

title: ham rice pinwheels
directions: In a medium bowl, cream the cheese until fluffy. Add rice, olives, onion, horseradish, pickle relish and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend well.
Spread each ham slice with 2 tablespoons of rice mixture.
Roll tightly.
Skewer each roll with toothpicks. Cover and chill for several hours.
Just before serving, cut into 1-inch slices.
Yields 32 pinwheels.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash in 1/2-inch boiling, salted water in covered pan over low heat until tender.
Drain and mash.
Saute onion in butter and add to squash.
Add salt, pepper, celery seed, pimento, 1 1/2 cups cheese and eggs.
Pour in greased, shallow baking dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs and 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Spread mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: hominy deluxe
directions: Cook until hominy is tender.

title: baked chicken and dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 hour in a 9 x 13 pan at 350°.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Blend eggs, Bisquick, margarine or butter, milk and salt. Stir in spinach and cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle over top the ham and green onions.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Top with 1 cup fresh mushrooms (sliced) and white sauce.

title: "my own" spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender (9 to 13 minutes).
Add rest of the ingredients.

title: squash-corn casserole
directions: Dice the squash and put in large mixing bowl.
Add drained can of corn, shallot, eggs, and cream cheese.
Mix well and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Make a white sauce by melting butter.
Add flour and cook until bubbly, stirring frequently about 1 minute.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened. Pour over squash mixture and gently mix.
You may top the casserole with buttered bread crumbs and a light sprinkle of pepper.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly, (30-45 minutes.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash, drain and slice berries.
Blend condensed milk and lemon juice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onions.
Season the meat to taste (salt, pepper, garlic, sweet basil, etc.).
Add remaining ingredients, except the Tater Tots and mix well.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish, top with Tater Tots and bake at 400° until the Tater Tots are browned.
Serve with melted cheese over the top, if desired.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well the flour and Worcestershire sauce. Add other ingredients and stir well. Good on chicken and pork.
If using on chicken, pour sauce over 4 to 8 chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
After 30 minutes, turn chicken and baste.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Grease 12 medium muffin cups. Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixer bowl. Beat in egg, sugar and 1 1/2 cups of the baking mix on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently, 2 minutes. Beat in remaining baking mix, then cinnamon, nutmeg and fruit on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally. Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full. Let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, and vanilla well.
Add dry ingredients, then apples and nuts.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pasta with lemon cream sauce
directions: In
a
saucepan,
cook	cream,	the
half and half, red pepper flakes and the rind over moderate heat until mixture is reduced to about 1 cup and thickened slightly.
While sauce is cooking,
boil the pasta in salted water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain
pasta.
In large serving bowl, combine pasta, sauce and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle pasta with parsley.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix well in order given and pour into shallow buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: pastry shell
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Moisten with cold milk until dough will leave the bowl.
Knead until smooth and roll out pie shell.

title: one bowl cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients; beat well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
One-half cup chopped black walnuts may be added, if desired.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done.

title: pickled wieners
directions: Bring to a boil.
Line jars with wieners and hot peppers (leave seeds in).
Pour hot syrup over wieners and peppers; cold pack 35 minutes.

title: zucchini sweet relish
directions: Grind squash, onions and red and green peppers.
Add the salt and let stand overnight.

title: raisin meringue pie
directions: Prepare and bake a 9-inch pie shell.
Cover the raisins with cold water; bring to a boil and drain.
Add the sugar, milk, butter and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add the chopped nuts.
Put in prepared pie shell.
Make meringue.

title: "chicken" casserole
directions: Drain and dice meat; combine meat, celery, onion, cheese and water chestnuts.
Stir in mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Cover and bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.
Remove cover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: cranberry fruited medley
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cranberry juice cocktail.
Pour about 1 cup of the gelatin mixture into mold and chill until slightly thickened.
Arrange some of the orange sections and grapes in a decorative pattern on the gelatin, pressing down gently.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Meanwhile, chill remaining gelatin until thickened. Dice remaining orange sections and cut grapes in half.
Stir into thickened gelatin. Spoon into mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold. Garnish with sugared grapes and orange slices, if desired.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in a 2-quart microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and continue to stir every 30 seconds for 2 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased pizza pan*.
Decorate with cherries.
Sprinkle on coconut.

title: aunt kim's cheesy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and remove.
Add soup, cheese and spaghetti to broth and bring to a boil.
Debone chicken and add to mixture. Simmer until cheese is melted and spaghetti is done.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread dough rise.
Pat out dough on 2 greased cookie sheets.
Layer meats and cheeses across middle of dough.
Put Parmesan on top.
Fold sides and ends over filling.
Turn over so folds and creases are on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian broiled scallops
directions: Place a scallop and a pineapple wedge at opposite ends of each strip of bacon.
Roll strips toward the center so that scallops and pineapple are wrapped in bacon.
Place 2 together on skewers. Broil until bacon is crisp, about 10 minutes, turning to brown on all sides.
Place 2 on each slice of toast and remove skewers carefully.
Serves 6.

title: cindy's sweet-n-sour steak
directions: Heat oil in medium to hot skillet; add steak, cut into thin strips, and brown on all sides, stirring frequently.
Lower heat; add celery and green peppers, cut into thin strips, and onion. Cook until celery is tender, but crunchy.
Add pineapple, syrup, vinegar and 8 ounces water.
Heat until bubbling.
Mix cornstarch with 3 tablespoons water; pour into bubbling mix and stir until desired thickness.
Pour over rice or noodles.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix butter, onion, sour cream
and mushroom soup with potatoes, then mix in shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Combine water and 100% Bran.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk and Nabisco (soaked).
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add all at once to Kellogg's All-Bran. Fold until mixed.
Bake in greased muffin pans 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
This will keep in refrigerator up to 7 weeks.

title: nachos(microwave)
directions: Place tortilla chips on microwavable plate.
Put about 1 teaspoon salsa on each chip.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave for 45 seconds on Medium or until cheese begins to melt.
Makes several plates full.

title: hearty bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Soak overnight.
Wash again and put beans in large Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add everything else.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer slowly until tender.
Add more water as they cook, if you need to.
Great served with slaw, cornbread and homemade applesauce.

title: crock-pot brunch casserole
directions: In skillet, lightly brown ground beef and onion in olive oil; drain well.
Place in well-greased crock-pot.
Stir in remaining ingredients except eggs, milk and cheese until well blended.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over other ingredients; stir well. Dust with additional nutmeg.
Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 9 hours or until firm.
Just before serving, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil margarine and water; add flour and stir.
Add eggs; beat until smooth and comes away from pan.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Top with slices of cheese and soup which has been mixed with wine.
Pour over chicken, then add stuffing on top.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients. Add coconut, pineapple and carrots.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli or spinach casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and strain.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and mix thoroughly.
Put crumbled crackers on top of slivered almonds.
Dot bits of butter evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Heat and stir sugar, syrup and water in 3-quart saucepan until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, blend in butter.
Stir often after reaches 230°.
Add nuts at 280°; stir constantly to hard crack stage (305°).
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in soda, mixing well.
Pour onto 2 cookie sheets.
Stretch thin by lifting and pulling from edges with forks.
Loosen from pans as soon as possible.
Break up.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: In large mixer bowl, dissolve jello with 1 cup hot water and 3/4 cup juice from drained mandarin orange segments.
Some cold water can be added if juice does not measure 3/4 cup.
Add orange segments and refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove when softly jelled and beat on high speed of electric mixer for 5 minutes or until all orange segments are crushed (will be liquidy).

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: 1. If you have the blues, read Psalm 27.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove skin from salmon steaks before cooking.
Boil salmon steaks in salted water for 7 to 8 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Flake to remove bones.
Saute onion and parsley in 1/2 stick margarine. Add to salmon.
Add crackers, egg and salt and pepper to taste. Mix and make into patties.
Fry to brown on both sides in butter or margarine.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix in large bowl the sugar and flour.
Bring to boil the oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.
Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar; blend well.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
This will be bubbly.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in a greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 1/8-inch).

title: parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Mix well and let cool to just warm.
Add eggs and flour. Mix all items together, beating vigorously.
Knead well.
Let rise until double.
Be sure to oil dough so it will not form a crust on outside as it rises.
A dampened cloth used to cover dough also helps.
Roll out on a lightly floured board.
Cut into shape and size desired.
Fold and let rise for 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.
Can be frozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Beat eggs in glass dish.
Add corn.
Cut butter into pats and mix with corn.
Add cheeses and mix.
Add flour last.
Mix well. Bake at 350° about 30 or 45 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Saute onion and pepper.
Grate cheese (save 1/2 of the cheese for topping).
Mix all together; pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato puff
directions: Mix potatoes, baking powder, egg and salt, then add flour, a little at a time, to thicken enough to spoon out.
Using the spoon, make into balls.
Drop into hot oil.
Turn until golden brown and drain.

title: broccoli and cheese rice
directions: Sear onions
and celery in thick skillet.
Add broccoli and 2 cups rice.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Mix and pour into baking dish.
Cook
minutes
(or until it bubbles) at 350°. Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into buttered 2 quart casserole.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cherry supreme chiffon cake
directions: In the first bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well and add the oil, cold water, egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef with onion and pepper. Drain and put in baking dish. Add soups and maybe a small amount of water (very little if any) Cover with frozen tater tots and cover with aluminum foil and bake for 50 minutes on 350°. Take out uncover and put the cheese on top. Cook 10 more minutes uncovered or until cheese melts.

title: low-fat pumpkin bread
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients until smooth.
Add the water, flour and baking soda.
Pour into 3 loaf pans, sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish seafoam salad
directions: Heat the pear juice and pour over lime jello.
While hot, pour into cream cheese which has been mashed with the cream.
When cool and thick, add the pears which have been mashed with a fork.
Add the whipped cream.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes in greased pan.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Peel 6 medium vine ripe firm tomatoes. Place in bowl. Sprinkle with seasonings and herbs. Combine oil and vinegar; pour over. Cover and chill an hour or more, occasionally spooning over dressing. Drain off dressing to serve. Snip over more parsley or chives.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles in boiling water 20 minutes.
Blend soup and milk into smooth sauce.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Drain noodles.
Layer 1 1/2 cups noodles, 1/3 cup meat and 1 cup vegetables in 2-quart casserole.
Pour in 1 cup sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes, then add cheese and bake 15 minutes more.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients for dressing.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Serve chilled.

title: anna's browned rice
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish, then add rice, broth and soup.
Cook with top on for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: creole gumbo
directions: Cut okra very fine and saute in oil until thick. Do not use iron skillet.
In a big pot make the roux.
Measure fat into the heavy pot.
Keep heat high to moderate; stir in flour and stir, stir, stir, to prevent burning until mixture becomes a medium brown color.
Then add onion and celery; cook on low until clear, 10-15 minutes.
Take time and success is yours.
Add tomatoes and water blending well.
Add okra and ham and all your seasonings; bring to a boil, then simmer for about an hour, adding more water if needed.
Add shellfish of your choice and simmer 30 minutes. Serve in soup bowls over boiled rice.

title: cheddar cheese rings
directions: You will need a Bundt pan.

title: snow cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: california sherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except powdered sugar, in a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 8 minutes.
Pour into greased tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar on top.

title: monkey cake
directions: Butter Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together. Cut each biscuit into fourths, then dip pieces in the mixture.
Layer in pan until all biscuits are gone.
Pour butter and rest of sugar and cinnamon mixture over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jambalya
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper, onion and garlic in large skillet and saute until beef is brown.
Combine with remaining ingredients into large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry chopped bacon until crisp; remove from fat.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in bacon drippings until tender.
Remove vegetables.

title: low-fat jambalaya
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Cook with oil, over high heat, in a Dutch oven.
Add the sausage and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Remove chicken and sausage; set aside.

title: cabbage creole
directions: In skillet, cook meat, onion and bell pepper until done.
Pour off grease.
In large pan, cook chopped cabbage and tomatoes until done.
Combine all; add Cheddar cheese soup.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, an hour or more.

title: coconut meringue pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, salt and milk.
Mix well.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, until warm.
Gradually add 1 cup of sugar and cornstarch to milk mixture, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and coconut.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Divide into 4 pieces and layer as follows:

1/4 cake, crumbled, strawberry filling, 1/4 Cool Whip, 1/4 pecans, 1/4 cake (crumbled), blueberry filling, 1/4 Cool Whip, 1/4 pecans, 1/4 cake (crumbled), pineapple, sliced bananas, 1/4 Cool Whip, 1/4 pecans, 1/4 cake (crumbled), cherry filling, Cool Whip and pecans.

title: jello cream cheese cake
directions: Mix and pat firmly into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: deluxe banana pudding
directions: Mix boxes instant vanilla pudding with milk.
Fold in sour cream and carton of whipped topping.
Cut desired amount of bananas and fold in.
Place layer of vanilla wafers in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish then layer of pudding mix.
Repeat.
Remaining topping may be spread on top. Chill.
Delicious.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Mix sugar and water.
Bring to a boil until sugar dissolves.
Let cool slightly.
Mix two mixtures together with lemonade and pineapple juice.
Freeze.
About 1 to 1 1/2 hours before serving, remove from freezer.
Cut or chop into small pieces and add 7-Up.
Serve as slush.

title: pear and cheese salad
directions: Wash lettuce; drain.
On small plates, place lettuce leaves. Add pear halves.
Fill with cottage cheese.
Add raisins and peanuts.
Enjoy.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: Place ribs, meaty side up, on rack in foil lined shallow pan. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour 1/3 of sauce on ribs.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° until until done, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, basting 3 or 4 times with remaining sauce.

title: creamy clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving juice.
Place onion, celery and potatoes in large saucepan.
Add reserved clam juice.
Add water to cover.
Cover and simmer over low heat 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Do not drain.

title: luscious leftovers(cold salad)
directions: About 15 minutes before serving, mix in a large bowl.
Combine ham and all ingredients with the mayonnaise.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Mix
together;
cook in 9 x 12-inch glass dish, sprayed with Pam at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool;
cut into pieces. Cut before
they get too cool because if not, the pieces will be a little difficult to get out of the dish.

title: easter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt onto wax paper. Beat together the butter and sugar in a large bowl until smooth. Beat in the egg, orange rind and juice.
Add the flour mixture, a third at a time.
Shape dough into a ball; flatten slightly.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate several hours.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into bunny or chick with 3-inch cutters.
Repeat with second half of dough.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: potato patties
directions: Mix potatoes, salt, onions, eggs and flour together.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: lemon impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter one 9-inch pie pan.
Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend at low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into prepared pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: chili cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes, in a bowl.
Place in a greased casserole dish and pour tomatoes over. (No additional liquid needed, cabbage cooks down.)
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes until cabbage is tender.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
In a bowl, process a small amount at a time in food processor at low speed.
Pour into serving bowl. Yields 3 cups.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Blend with mixer or spoon the flour, cocoa, soda, salt, oats and nuts.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: okra pickles
directions: Wash and trim tops of okra, then pack in pint jars.
To each jar, add salt, garlic, mustard seed and hot pepper.
Bring white vinegar (enough for each jar) to a boil and pour over okra.
Seal immediately.
Let stand at least 3 weeks before serving.
Better when chilled.

title: grandmother's applesauce cake
directions: Mix all together in one bowl.
Pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake in a 250° to 300° oven at least 1 hour or until it comes from the sides a little.
Can be made ahead and freezes well for holidays.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter chips; stir just to distribute chips throughout mixture.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours, or until firm. Remove from pan; peel off foil.
Cut into squares.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen pieces or about 2 pounds.

title: barbecued turkey drumsticks
directions: Arrange drumsticks in skillet.
Season with salt and pepper; add water.
Cover tightly; simmer, turning occasionally, 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
If all water evaporates, add small amounts at a time.

title: aunt helen's bow ties
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sweet cream.
Mix with whiskey and vanilla.
Mix flour and salt to eggs and cream together.
Add another 1/2 cup of flour, if needed.
Roll out thin and cut into 2-inch strips, about 4 inches long.
Put slit in middle and loop one end through the other and pull.

title: corned beef potato salad
directions: In large bowl, toss potatoes, meat, pickles, celery and onion. In covered jar, shake oil, vinegar, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour over meat mixture and toss.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, mix sour cream and horseradish.
Pour over meat mixture and toss.
Season to taste. Serve on crisp greens and garnish with cherry tomatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove all skin and big bones from salmon.
Flake salmon and mix with other ingredients until crackers are moist.
(If you have time, refrigerate 30 minutes.)
Dip by rounded tablespoon and form into 10 patties.
Fry over medium heat until brown and crisp. Serve hot.

title: trail mix
directions: Put all ingredients together in a bowl; mix together.
Makes as much as you desire.
Serve.

title: fruit bars
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add sugar.
Mix.
Combine margarine and eggs (in blender).
Stir into dry ingredients.
Add nuts, dates, coconut and raisins.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 16 bars.
Cut while hot.

title: crabbies-appetizers
directions: Mix softened margarine and cheese until
well blended.
Add mayonnaise and blend well.
Add well drained crab, lemon juice and garlic powder; mix well.
Spread on 12 English muffin halves.
Cut each half into fourths.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: steak roll-ups
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; drain.
Add thyme, marjoram, green onions, pimento, mushrooms and margarine; set aside.
Place meat on waxed paper and pound it with mallet or other heavy object until flattened to a thickness of 1/4 inch. Cut into 6 pieces.
Spread with rice mixture.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Brown in shortening; pour off grease.
Add soup mixture and 1 cup of water.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove from heat to a warm platter.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir into soup mixture.
Cook until thick. Serve over steak rolls.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Lay chicken breasts in baking dish; cover with Swiss cheese. Mix soup, margarine and milk together and cover over chicken. Sprinkle with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for an hour or until chicken is tender.

title: baked ham and egg brunch casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish (9 x 11-inch); spread with 1 cup bread cubes.
Sprinkle with ham, cheese, onion and rest of bread.
Beat eggs with milk, butter and mustard.
Pour on top.
Refrigerate overnight!
Bring to room temperature and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix milk, pineapple, vanilla and Cool Whip. Add lemon juice last.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill for 3 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: arkansas bars
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs until creamy; add vanilla and flour and blend.
Spread evenly on large greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cookie dough.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°. Cut into bars while warm.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and blend well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(It's done when toothpick inserted comes out clean.)

title: overnight cabbage salad
directions: Shred/slice all vegetables thinly (the food processor is perfect for this).
Mix vinegar, vegetable oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.

title: scrumptious banana pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan and slowly cook on top of stove until thick.

title: arkansas sweet and sour cabbage slaw
directions: Cut or shred cabbage.
Shred onion and sprinkle over cabbage. Sprinkle 1 cup of sugar (less 2 tablespoons) over this.
Do not stir.
Heat last 6 ingredients to boiling.
Pour over cabbage (do not stir and cover quickly).
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites in bowl until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and salt.
Beat until medium-stiff peaks form.
Fold in 1 cup sugar gently, using 25 strokes.
Sift 1/2 cup sugar and flour together 3 times.
Fold into egg whites, 1/4 at a time, using 15 strokes after each addition.
Fold in flavoring, using 10 strokes.
Spoon into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Cut through batter with knife. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Invert on funnel to cool.
Loosen edges with knife.
Remove from pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw frozen spinach.
Rinse, drain and squeeze out excess juice.
Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl and chill for 2 hours.
Serve in hollowed out round bread (such as rye/pumpernickel) with scooped out bread, cut into chunks.
I sometimes put a small bowl in the center of the bread and put the dip in the bowl.
This way the rest of the bread can be later broken up to use with the dip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together eggs, oil and sugar.
Add zucchini, vanilla and nutmeats.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder into mixture; mix well.
Use 2 pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch or 8 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch, greased.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and spices.
Blend in shortening, sweet potatoes and milk.
Should make a stiff dough. Flour counter surface.
Pat dough to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits with small juice glass or 3-inch cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked pork chops & potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large skillet, saute chops in shortening until browned on both sides; drain on paper towels. In buttered 2-qt. oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes, onion, and browned pork chops. In small bowl, combine Lipton mix and water; pour over vegetables and meat. Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: venison delight
directions: Roll meat in flour and brown in skillet with lard.
Pour off most of the grease.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Continue beating and add vanilla and sour cream.
Sift together and add the soda, salt, baking powder and flour.
Roll out on heavily floured board, rather thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Pick and wash berries, pick out the solid ones and set aside. Mash the soft berries, set aside.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and stir into the soft, mashed strawberries.
Cook over low heat until thick and kind of clear looking.
Set aside.
Halve the firm berries into a cooked pie shell, pour the cooked mixture over them.
Let cool and serve with fresh whipped cream.

title: microwave rocky road candy(makes about 2 dozen)
directions: Combine chocolate
chips
and
half
and half in medium bowl. Microwave
at
Medium-high	(70%) until chocolate chips are melted, 1
to
minutes,	stirring
once during cooking. Stir in vanilla and remaining ingredients until coated.
Press into greased square baking dish, 8 x 8-inches.
Chill.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut chickens into pieces.
Place flour, corn meal, salt, pepper and paprika in paper sack.
Shake until well mixed.
Place 2 pieces of chicken in flour sack at a time.
Shake so that all chicken is coated well.
Put the melted butter in bottom of baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn chicken several times during baking time.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Cook chicken breast separately; cut up.
Cook tortellini separately.
Chop scallions to desired amount.
Cook all ingredients in chicken broth; let simmer.
Add tortellini.

title: windows on the water(lobster-stuffed potato)
directions: Lightly coat potato skins with a small amount of olive oil and bake at 375° for an hour.
Let cool, then cut in half and scoop out pulp into mixing bowl.
Melt the butter in a saute pan and add the onion with a dash of salt and pepper.
Saute until onion is translucent.
Stir in lobster and wine and bring to boil, stirring frequently, until liquid is boiled away.
Add sour cream and heavy cream and remove from heat.
Combine pulp, lobster, cheese and scallion and mix well.
Stuff potatoes skins with equal parts of the filling and bake at 400° until hot.
Serves four.

title: rice krispie date cookies
directions: Cook butter, eggs, sugar and dates until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour over nuts and Rice Krispies that are mixed in a large bowl.
Mix and let cool.
Form in small balls and roll in coconut.

title: blackberry and zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except berries and zucchini until just blended. Fold in the berries and zucchini. Turn into a sprayed loaf pan (with vegetable spray) and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Check after the first 45 minutes to prevent browning too quickly. Makes 15 slices per loaf.
Contains 172 calories, 31 gm. carbohydrates, 4.3 gm. fat, 0 mg. cholesterol, 112 mg. sodium, 189 mg. potassium and 4.1 gm. protein per slice.

title: cement icing
directions: Combine flour, salt and milk in saucepan; cook over medium heat until thick.
Chill in refrigerator while baking cake. Cream together with electric mixer until fluffy the Crisco, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour paste and beat well. This will ice a 2-layer cake and is also good as a filling for cupcakes, cream puffs, etc.

title: southern peanut pie
directions: In
large
bowl beat eggs until foamy.	Add sugar, corn syrup, butter,
salt
and
vanilla.
Blend.
Stir in peanuts. Pour into pie crust.	Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes (until set).	Serve warm or cold.

title: mezzetti
directions: Heat shortening in skillet.
Add ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Cook until slightly brown.
Add chili powder and garlic salt.
Sprinkle noodles over top.
Add water.
Mix soups together and pour over meat mixture.
Cover.
Bring to steaming, then turn to low heat for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over mixture. Cook another 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli tortellini salad
directions: Boil tortellini for 15 minutes, then drain and let cool. Combine with other ingredients in bowl; refrigerate for 2 hours. Serves 2.

title: spiced carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl of an electric mixer, beat sugar and salad oil for 2 minutes.
Beat in one egg at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour mixture, beating just until blended.
Mix in carrots and 1 cup of the pecans.
Pour into two greased waxed paper lined 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jean's chicken roll
directions: After chicken is cooked and cut up, add remaining ingredients along with small amount of stock from chicken.
Cook until vegetables are just done.
Let cool.
Make 1 1/2 recipes Bisquick biscuits, roll in large rectangle and put in chicken mixture.
Roll up and put on large cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°. Serve with chicken gravy.

title: inside-out chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Place in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cake cool in pan for 15 minutes before inverting onto serving plate.
