Dust with powdered sugar before serving.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak red beans overnight.
Rinse before cooking.
Saute vegetables in large pot.
Add sausage or ham.
Add rinsed red beans.
Cover beans with water and bring to a boil.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours until beans are soft.
Add salt and pepper.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread can of fruit pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dry cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle melted margarine over top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour or until top is brown.

title: cheese spread
directions: With a mixer, blend together cream cheese and butter.
While mixing, blend in small amounts of Cheddar cheese spread.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth and creamy.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: alpine potatoes
directions: Heat 1/4 cup butter and soup. Blend in sour cream and onions. Stir in potatoes.
Place in 9 x 13 pan.
Place crushed potato chips on top. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian sausage soup with tortellini
directions: If sausage comes in casing, remove and make into little meat balls.
In 5-quart Dutch oven, or soup pot, brown sausage. Remove sausage and drain, reserving
1 tablespoon to saute onions and garlic until onions are tender.
Add all ingredients except tortellini.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, until all vegetables are tender.
I sometimes shorten cooking time by cooking just the vegetables with a little water added in the microwave for 10 minutes and then adding to the soup broth.
Skim any fat from soup.
Stir in tortellini and simmer, covered, an additional 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread and you have a complete meal soup.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix water, Miracle Whip and sugar together.
Add to macaroni; stir.
Add rest and stir well.

title: hot lettuce
directions: Place egg and flour in saucepan; mix well and add sugar. Heat; add
milk, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add bacon and vinegar; heat thoroughly.
Pour over lettuce and toss.
Serve over fried potatoes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer ingredients in order.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: baked rice
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Cover again and continue baking 30 minutes more.
Serves 10.

title: strawberries and cream dessert
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water; mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 2 cups pudding mixture into 4-quart round serving bowl; top with half the cake cubes, half the strawberries, half the preserves and half the remaining pudding mixture.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding mixture.
Garnish with additional strawberries and almonds.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine in ovenproof 13 x 9-inch casserole in slow oven.
Mix potatoes, onion, cheese, sour cream and soup and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix corn flakes with 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Put on top of potatoes and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2 small, unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until slightly brown and set.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Scald milk; mix dry ingredients together.
Add hot milk, stirring constantly.
Cook in a double boiler until smooth and thick, about 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add a small amount of hot mixture to them.
Add this quickly to remainder of hot mixture and cook 3 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten egg and evaporated milk. Add bananas. Mix well. Add flour, baking powder and vanilla. Mix well. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Butter a casserole. Layer creamed corn and whole corn. Add Ritz crackers and butter. Salt and pepper. Drizzle a little cream on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter ice cream
directions: Melt margarine and add crumbs.
Put in bottom of pan and chill.
Let ice cream soften and mix in peanut butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: airport casserole
directions: Brown the hamburg, onion and pepper in the margarine.
Then add the soups and rice and mix together.
Turn into an ungreased casserole.
It doesn't need a topping and do not use a cover.
You can bake it for 3 or 4 hours at 250° or 275° or about 3 hours at 300°.
You can also substitute a can of undiluted celery soup for one of the soups mentioned.

title: spam enchiladas
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, reserving 1 to 2 cups cheese for topping.
Heat 2 cans enchilada sauce in frying pan.
Separate tortillas and drop in enchilada sauce for a second or two, to soften enough to roll.
Place tortillas on a cookie sheet with sides and put 2 tablespoons of meat mixture on each tortilla and roll.
Push to back of pan.
Continue to make enchiladas until all of meat mixture is used.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce on top of rolled tortillas and sprinkle well with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.
Serves 12 or more.

title: overnight ham casserole
directions: Saute bacon. Break into pieces and return to pan. Remove half of the bacon fat.
To the remaining fat, add the cubed ham and 1/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle flour and mix well.
Gradually add the milk and cook. Season with salt and pepper (1/8 teaspoon).
Set aside. Beat eggs into evaporated milk.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt. Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large skillet. Add egg mixture and scramble until firm.

title: macaroni au-gratin with vegetables
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water, salted, until tender.
Drain and rinse.
While macaroni is cooking, melt butter in large saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk and vegetable liquid, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Add grated cheese, macaroni and vegetables; mix well.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender, then season with salt and pepper.
Slice chicken.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Arrange on bottom of buttered baking dish. Lay chicken on broccoli and spread noodles on top of the chicken. Blend together soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle bread crumbs lightly over top of casserole and dot with butter.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine ingredients using 1/2 of the onions.
Bake in casserole for 25 minutes at 350°, then add remaining French fried onions and brown 5 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt chocolate as for other dipped candies.
However much you want to make.
Mix peanut butter (one jar makes a nice batch) and powdered sugar (1/2 to 1 pound), so you can roll into small balls. Use toothpick to dip in chocolate.
Place in candy papers or on wax paper.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease pan. Roll out dough. Poke holes in dough. Put in oven for about 7 minutes until golden brown. Take out. Brown sausage in microwave for a couple of minutes. Put in bottom of pan. Scramble eggs with fork. Season. Put to side. Cut up onion and put over sausage (optional) the pizza cheese. Pour eggs over cheese. Sprinkle oregano and Parmesan. Bake by directions on the crust can.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in blender for 2 minutes until well blended.

title: chicken a la can
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole or baking dish.
Extra Minute rice may be added.
Bake at 350°
until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and set aside. Pour cooking oil into a large bowl. Add sugar and eggs.
Beat well.

title: country swiss steaks
directions: Slice the meat
into steaks 1-inch thick, 3-inches wide and 5-inches long.
Place
the
cooking
oil
in
a frypan and heat. Roll the steaks
in the flour.
Remove and place in the frypan. Cook,
turning
occasionally
until
done
and brown. Remove from frypan
and
place
in a roasting pan.
Cover with onions, tomatoes and tomato juice.
Cover and bake in preheated 325° oven for 2
to
hours
or until the steaks are tender.
Mix 2 tablespoons
of
flour
with a small amount of water.
Make a smooth mixture and add to the steaks, stirring gently.
Cook for another
to 10 minutes and the steaks are ready to serve. Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: ham delites
directions: Split dinner rolls and put 1 slice of cheese and 1 slice of ham in each roll.
Put in a baking dish or leave in the aluminum pan the rolls came in.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over top of rolls.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: waterless  carrots
directions: Place carrots, sugar, margarine, salt and pepper in tight fitting pan on low heat for 15-20 minutes.
This is one serving.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Cook rhubarb in water until tender; strain.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add juices; cool.
Add 3 quarts cold water when ready to serve.

title: flagagan sauerkraut and ribs
directions: Place meat on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with kraut.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and top with French onion soup (do not dilute).
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours or until tender.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Cool and toss with lettuce, beans and cheese.
Mix with dressing.

title: birds nest cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon into a large mixing bowl. Make a well in center and pour remaining ingredients into well. Combine. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake is done.

title: pasta salad (2)
directions: Mix well and chill.
Then add 1 green pepper, 1 red pepper, 1 red onion, 1 tomato, 1 head of broccoli, 8 oz. Cheddar cheese. Chop vegetables and add to pasta mixture.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook 20 minutes on medium-high or until potatoes are tender. Then add 1 can of Carnation milk.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water.
Shut heat off.
Let chicken sit in water for 10 minutes.
Cut into small pieces.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: turkey breast supreme
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add turkey; brown on both sides.
Add onion; saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in soup, diluted with water, and season with pepper.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes, turning once.
Remove turkey to heated serving dish.
Add cheese to sauce remaining in skillet; stir until melted.
Pour cheese sauce over turkey; serve with cooked white rice.
Garnish with additional green onion if desired.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate. In a large bowl, cream together Crisco and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat 1 minute. Add chocolate and 1/2 cup walnuts. Turn batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 cup walnuts. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: deluxe cheesecake
directions: Prepare graham cracker mixture.
Press into lightly greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese in mixer bowl for 2 to 3 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar and eggs gradually.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Mix sour cream, remaining 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Spread over cheesecake.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Chill until firm.
Topping will be soft when warm and firm when chilled.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: almond powdered butter cookies
directions: Beat butter for about 20 minutes until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar, whiskey and vanilla.
Slowly add almonds.
Gradually add flour until dough is soft.
Dough could be chilled for an hour, but not necessary.
Roll into balls and bake 15 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool, then sift powdered sugar generously over each.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, cover onions with water.
Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
Drain.
Put onions in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix egg, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spinach salad
directions: Put oil, sugar, mustard and salt in blender.
Add onion juice, with blender running, remove cover and add vinegar.

title: easy steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Salt and pepper steak and place in crock-pot.
Add celery, green onion, parsley flakes and garlic powder.
Pour soup and water on top.
Cook on low overnight.

title: copper pennies
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients, except carrots.
Bring to a boil only.
Remove from heat.
Drain carrots and add to the liquid mixture.
Chill at least 1 day before serving.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Firmly shape meat mixture in 2-quart oblong baking dish, into 8 x 4-inch loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until meat is no longer pink (160°). Drain off fat, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings. Combine remainder of can of soup, 1/4 cup water and reserved drippings in small pan; heat. Serve over meat loaf. Makes 6 servings.

title: julia's instant potato lefse
directions: Scald milk, cream and butter.
Pour over potatoes and salt, then cool real good.
Add flour.
Makes 20 lefse.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss all except potato chips. Top with potato chips. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and flour.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: buck-a-roo beef skillet
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained can of tomatoes, undrained kidney beans, uncooked rice, green pepper, chili powder, garlic salt, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts.
Top with chips around edge.

title: jell-o salad
directions: Dissolve jell-o and set 2 cups of jell-o aside.
Drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple and Jell-o and strawberries. Refrigerate, when almost set take out of refrigerator.
Put a layer of marshmallows and some nuts on top of the Jell-o.
Spread whipped Dream Whip on top (1/2 of Dream Whip).
Mix rest of Dream Whip with the 2 cups of Jell-o which was set aside.
Put on top.
Then sprinkle with nuts.

title: miss mary's cabbage casserole
directions: Cook
the
first
3 ingredients in lightly salted water until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.	Slowly add milk; stir	until thickened.
Add
cheese;
blend
until
melted. Preheat oven
Layer the drained cabbage mixture and cheese
sauce	in
a greased casserole.	Make several layers, ending with
sauce.
Bake until
bubbly.
Top with crumbs (we use cornbread crumbs that are sprinkled with poultry seasoning or you
could
use
cornbread stuffing
mix).
Return to oven until lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese with spaghetti.
Place in 10-inch buttered casserole.
Add cottage cheese on top.
Top with ground beef.
Pour spaghetti sauce or stewed tomatoes over the top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese when almost done.

title: laster's best chicken casserole
directions: Mix everything, except chicken, Doritos and cheese.
In a 3-quart casserole dish, layer Doritos, soup mixture and chicken, repeating layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes to melt cheese.

title: banana muffins
directions: Sift
dry ingredients into mixing bowl; cut shortening. Combine egg
and
milk and add to the dry mixture.
Add banana and stir just enough to combine.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar over each.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet with metal handle or heat-proof serving dish.
Add oil, half of the parsley, garlic powder, salt, cayenne and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add shrimp, tossing gently with butter mixture.
Arrange in skillet in single layer.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley and garnish with lemon wedges.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: *This is a good recipe for using leftover Thanksgiving turkey!

title: bubbly apple drink
directions: For each serving, place 1 scoop of lemon, lime or orange sherbet or vanilla ice cream in a tall glass.
Fill with cranberry juice cocktail, chilled.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Prepare cream sauce in double boiler.
Pour over carrots and onions.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: banana cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening until soft, gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Blend well after each addition.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle tops with cinnamon, sugar, chopped nuts or coconut.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: hawaiian cookies(makes 3 to 4 dozen)
directions: Cream oleo and sugars.
Blend in egg, pineapple and vanilla. Sift flour with other dry ingredients. Add to cream mixture and mix well.
Stir in pecans and coconuts, if desired. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: apricot salad
directions: Let Jell-O begin to set; mix in remaining ingredients.

title: potato breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in potatoes, cheese and seasonings. Turn into buttered 10-inch glass pie plate or shallow casserole. Scatter bacon on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Can refrigerate overnight.
Place cold dish in oven and bake
at 350° for 40 minutes.
If baking immediately, reduce by 10 minutes.

title: reduced fat cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Grind or chop walnuts.
Cut grapes in half, removing seeds if necessary.
Place the ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and pineapple.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Add whipped topping just before serving.
Yield:
Approximately 20 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Prepare and cut chicken in pieces.
Let stand in water while preparing casserole.
Grease a long baking dish with butter. Sprinkle rice in dish evenly.
Mix the two cans of soup and milk in mixing bowl.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken on top of soup. Sprinkle 1 envelope onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover dish tightly with foil.
Place in a 325° to 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: rhubarb cake and topping
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar together and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together and blend well.
Stir in rhubarb mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: basic vegetable rice
directions: Cook rice using chicken stock.
Fifteen minutes before rice is done, add your vegetables (chopped) and seasonings and herbs. When rice is done you may need to add more chicken stock if rice is too dry.

title: shirley's nonstick baking pan coating
directions: Mix solid and oil Crisco slowly.
Add flour.
Coat pans.
No need to add anything else.
Refrigerate remainder in covered jar for future use.
Keeps 3 months.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion; set aside.
Brown ground beef until crumbly, then drain.
Combine bacon, onion, ground beef and all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Great as a side dish at a barbecue, but can also serve as a main dish.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, honey, paprika and mustard together.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and shake well. Refrigerate.
Great for salads but especially good on apple salad or spinach salad.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in cranberries and pineapple.
Pour in 2-quart flat pan and refrigerate until firm.
Blend in softened cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over salad.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: grandma oliver's fruit cake
directions: Mix together the eggs and brown sugar; add oil, then add all of the fruit and 1 cup of flour.
Add the nuts and grape juice and finally the 4 cups of remaining flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes several fruit cakes depending on the size of pans used.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except dry bread crumbs, butter and tartar sauce.
Shape into 8 patties, gently squeeze out excess liquid.
Coat each side in bread crumbs.
Cook in butter or Crisco until golden brown on each side.
Serve with tartar sauce and lemon wedges.

title: frozen black cherry cups
directions: Combine pineapple, sour cream, yogurt and lemon juice.
Gently stir in cherries, banana and pecans.
Spoon into 12 paper baking cups in muffin pans.
Cover and freeze for 2 to 4 hours.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Beat 3 egg yolks.
Add rind of 1 lemon and the juice of 2 lemons.
Add can of condensed milk and stir until thick.
Crush 1/2 box of wafers and put on bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour mixture over crumbs, then spread the whipped cream over mixture.
Add the remaining crushed wafers and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pot, bring 5 cups water to a boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Prepare, then add the carrots; prepare and add the onion; prepare and add the potatoes.
After potatoes are just tender, add margarine and let melt.
Mix together 1 cup milk and flour and stir into soup, stirring constantly (will be very thick).
Add 1 1/2 cups more milk and let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over cucumbers. Stir together and chill any leftovers.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add boiling water.
Add pineapple, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
When partly jelled, add Dream Whip.

title: peanut butter mallow krispie bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup butter and egg together.
Press in ungreased 9 x 19-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes.
Pour marshmallows on top and bake 1 to 2 minutes.
Melt syrup, 1/4 cup butter, vanilla and peanut butter chips in microwave.
Stir in Rice Krispies and salted peanuts.
Spread on top of marshmallows with spoon.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: salmon pancakes
directions: Combine grated onion with mashed potatoes.
Add salmon and egg.
Add bread crumbs to mixture so that it is firm, but not dry. Shape it flat on large spatula and slide it into preheated oil in frying pan.
Fry about 1 minute on each side until brown.
Serve hot.
(Can use leftover cooked fish instead of salmon.)

title: broccoli-cheese cornbread
directions: Press broccoli between paper towels to remove excess moisture. Combine eggs, cornbread, onion, cheese, butter and seasonings. Stir well, then stir in broccoli.
Pour mixture into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly and eat.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; add oil, carrots and eggs one at a time.
Pour into floured cake pan and bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: sweet potatoes with pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil sweet potatoes until done.
Peel the potatoes.
In a mixing bowl, mash the sweet potatoes.
Add butter or margarine, sugar and crushed pineapples.
Mix until blended well.
Place in pan and then in the oven for 15 minutes. Let cool.
Serve.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add one egg at a time; beat well.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to sugar mixture.
Sift flour and salt.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately, a little at a time, mixing well after each addition. Begin and end with flour.
Combine vinegar and soda; add to batter. Pour into 2 (8-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cakes tests done.
Let cool and split layers.

title: large crowd casserole
directions: Stir well until all is blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Even better reheated!!

title: chili potatoes
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and set aside.
Saute onion until golden brown.
In a 3-quart microwave dish, add potatoes, chili powder, butter, salt, pepper and sauteed onion.
Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 15 minutes until tender.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Add crumbled bacon and serve.

title: casserole
directions: Place potatoes in large baking dish and put green beans on top. Sprinkle celery and onion on top.
Mix soup and milk together and pour 2/3 over green beans.
Place steak on top and spread remaining soup mixture on top.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° until done.
Remove foil last 15 minutes to brown meat slightly.
(Corn may be substituted for green beans and/or pork chops for steak.)

title: butter coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar, creaming well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour, drained pineapple and coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter banana sandwich
directions: Spread bread with mayonnaise and peanut butter.
Add sliced banana and lettuce.
Sprinkle with wheat germ for extra nutrition.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Put pineapple in baking dish. Add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Mix egg, sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
(Microwave on High 3 or 4 minutes or until thick.) Pour over pineapple mixture. Spread grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 15 minutes).

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well, then add flour and mix.
Stir in cornflakes, oats and coconut. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: garlic-spinach dip
directions: Cook frozen spinach according to package directions; drain. Blend or process garlic 5 to 10 seconds.
Add cooked spinach, milk, salt and hot pepper sauce; cover and blend or process until smooth.
Add cheeses; cover and blend until smooth.
Transfer all to saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat 4 to 5 minutes. Transfer dip to small serving bowl.
Sprinkle with chopped tomato. Serve with toasted pita wedges or crackers.

title: smoky beef salami
directions: Mix together thoroughly; cover and chill 24 hours or longer. Divide mixture into 4 amounts.
Roll each into long logs.
Place and roll into handiwipes tightly and tie ends.
Bake at 225° for 4 hours.
Use broiler pan so grease will run off.
Unroll after cooked.
Pat with toweling to get grease off.

title: rice salad vinaigrette
directions: Cook the carrots and green beans in a minimum of salted water until they are barely tender and drain immediately.
Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl and toss together.
Combine the cheese, olive oil, vinegar and seasonings and whisk until smooth.
Pour the dressing over the salad, toss until everything is thoroughly combined and put in the refrigerator to chill for several hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pasta sauce
directions: *Or, 1 (12 ounce) tomato sauce and 1 cup water or tomato paste and whole tomatoes and little water.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: poor man's frosting(mock whipped cream icing)
directions: Cook the flour and milk until thick; cool.
Cream the sugar, butter and vanilla well; add to cooled mixture.
Beat with mixer until right consistency to spread.
Should resemble whipped cream.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Add other ingredients and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Season to taste.

title: christmas candy
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add milk.
Gradually add 2 pounds sifted powdered sugar, vanilla, and pecans.
Mix using hands.
Mix in salt.
Make into balls about the size of walnuts.
Let stand 1 or 2 hours or until they become a little dry.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Add 1/4 pound or 1 block of paraffin.
Be careful, it is very flammable.
With a fork, put each ball into chocolate mixture, one or two at a time.
When completely covered, remove to an oiled or buttered platter.
Let stand until they harden.

title: holiday punch
directions: Whip lemonade, pineapple and juice and strawberries in blender at high speed.
Add ginger ale and pour over ice.

title: taco chicken
directions: Mix soups and tomatoes together.
In casserole dish (7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch), put a layer of chicken.
Spread part of soup mix over chicken, 1/2 of cheese and a layer of Doritos.
Repeat with rest of ingredients same way.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: baked sandwiches
directions: Fry bacon crisp and break in pieces.
Mix with dried beef. Put on bun.
Mix relish, onion and chili sauce.
Put this on top of bacon and dried beef.
Add American cheese on top.
Wrap in foil and put in oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: aunt rosie's sweet and sour cucumber salad
directions: Coat noodles with oil while still warm.
Mix together next 7 ingredients.
Slice cucumbers and onions very thin.
Mix all together at least 4 hours before serving.
Overnight is best. Cucumbers and onions may be added as eaten.

title: twinkie cakes
directions: Cut Twinkies longways and lay in an oval baking dish.
Cover Twinkies with cherry pie filling; top with Cool Whip.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon together.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the Ritz crackers and margarine.
Pour in baking dish.
Crush the Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Melt margarine and drizzle on top of crackers. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: pan, pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix with eggs, water and oil.
Drain pineapple.
Mix all together in long cake pan.
Grease and flour first.
Pour in and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
While cake is still hot, mix icing. Put sugar and margarine in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Take and pour over hot cake.
First take a knife, put holes in cake.
Mix nuts and coconut icing.
Pour over cake; let cool.

title: christmas balls
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and vanilla; add sugar, creaming mixture until light and fluffy.
Blend in water, then stir in flour, mixing well.
Add pecans.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in colored sugar.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake for 20 minutes or until firm to the touch.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: dutch slaw
directions: Place shredded cabbage in large bowl.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Cover with ice and water; let stand 1 hour. Soften the cream cheese; add cream and 2 tablespoons vinegar, a little at a time, beating until smooth.
Season with sugar, dry mustard and salt.
Drain cabbage and dry well in paper towels. Combine with diced apples; pour dressing over salad and toss. Garnish with apple slices and pepper strips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients except pecans in mixer.
Chill.
Shape into 2-inch balls and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.
Yields 2 balls.

title: corn casserole
directions: Dump everything in a bowl; mix, then pour into buttered pan. Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients; then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° until a toothpick comes out clean (about 1 hour).

title: crescent cream cheese squares
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Roll one package of crescent rolls out on wax paper and place in bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice together and spread on top of dough.
Roll out second package of crescent rolls and place on top of cream cheese filling.
Brush top with egg white.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool and cut in squares.
Best if done the night before needed. Refrigerate.

title: vanishing oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat together margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well. Stir in raisins and nuts; mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: cream cheese and pecan spread
directions: Mix pineapple to softened cream cheese.
Add pecans and mix. Use knife to spread on any type of cracker.

title: sausage-corn chowder
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add the sausage and combine with remaining ingredients.
Heat on low until cheese melts.

title: gold coast pork chops
directions: In a skillet, use shortening if needed, brown chops; drain. Stir in soup, 1/4 cup water, carrots, onion and sage.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add green pepper; cook 15 minutes more or until done, stirring occasionally.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: I boil the hamburger for a few minutes and then drain to remove excess fat.
Combine all ingredients and simmer until sauce is desired consistency.

title: chicken with rice(from the kitchen of sarah surina.)
directions: Flour pieces of chicken and brown in small amount of oil. Melt butter in shallow baking dish or pan.
Cover bottom with layer of rice.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Add mushroom soup and chicken broth.
Add water.
Salt and pepper to taste. Spread soup over chicken and spread it around.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream pies(chocolate, banana cream & coconut cream)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, and salt in heavy saucepan.
Add milk, and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Lower heat, cover and cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.

title: fruited caribbean pork chops
directions: Combine flour, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Rub mixture on both sides of all chops.
Brown chops in oil on medium high.
Drain pineapple juice from pineapple chunks.
Set chunks aside.
Combine juice with 3/4 cup pineapple juice, water, brown sugar, dried onion and tomato paste.
Stir until well blended. Place chops in crock-pot.
Pour juice mixture over chops. Sprinkle raisins over top.
Cover and cook on high 3 to 3 1/2 hours or on low 6 to 7 hours.
Add pineapple chunks.
Cook on high 10 minutes.

title: deluxe spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all the ingredients, stirring well. Store mixture in an airtight container.
To serve, place 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon mixture in a cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water, stirring well.
Yields 14 cups.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix everything together but chicken.
Place chicken in shallow pan or baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
(For glass pans, bake at 325°.)
Serves 4.

title: nana's brownies
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt in large bowl and set aside.
In saucepan put butter, water and cocoa and bring to boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla. Pour into greased cookie sheet with sides and bake at 400° for 12 - 15 minutes.
Frosting:
Put 1/3 c. buttermilk, 1/4 c. cocoa and a stick of butter in saucepan and bring to boil.
While boiling add 1 lb powdered sugar, pinch of salt and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Pour over warm brownies.
These are my Grandmother's brownies and they are heavenly!!

title: egg bake
directions: Cook meat.
Spread into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: penthouse chicken
directions: Melt butter in 14-inch Dutch oven.
Add the chicken and cook until all the meat is white, turning occasionally.	Stir in tomato soup
and spaghetti sauce.
Cook 1 1/2 hour with 14 coals on top and 14 coals on the bottom.
Maintain 14 coals on top and bottom by replenishing as needed.

title: pound cake mississippi style
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and rum extract.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour that has been sifted three times.
Add milk in small portions as other ingredients are added to improve texture.
Bake approximately at 275° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.
Bake in a large tube pan or 2 smaller ones.

title: breakfast coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually until very light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Add flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, Karo syrup, butter and nuts; but do not stir. Cook until amber in color.
Remove from fire.
Add water and soda. Stir and pour over one gallon of popped corn. This makes 20 popcorn balls, or stir and let loose like cracker jacks.

title: chinese hamburger chow mein
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Drain and then add all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Chinese noodles and bake about 15 minutes longer or if you like, you can mix the noodles with the first mixing of ingredients and bake 1 hour.

title: white trash
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Mix cereal, etc., and pour chocolate over
it.
Stir
well.
Spread
on wax paper to cool. Break into pieces and refrigerate.	Can be frozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Mash together avocado, lemon juice, salt and pepper; set aside.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; set aside.
Layer bean dip, avocado mixture and sour cream mixture in serving bowl.
Sprinkle on tomatoes, onions and olives on top with cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: no yeast babka
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add the egg yolks.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Spoon in slowly the beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 9-inch tube pan for 40 to 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: no-peek stew
directions: In sprayed roaster, place meat.
Cut into small pieces.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes.
Cut into chunks.
Add to meat.
Add soups and beans.
Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°.
Do not peek.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Make white sauce by combining margarine, flour, salt and milk. Cook over medium heat until thickened. Drain peas and mushrooms. Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole with onion and almonds. Pour sauce over peas. Garnish with pimiento strips. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all veggies. Add, stir in, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper. Pour into buttered 6 x 10 dish. Melt butter and stir with crushed crackers. Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chaurice sausage cornbread dressing
directions: Saute the vegetables in the butter until half cooked.
Add the seasonings and Chaurice sausage; stir well. Blend the cornbread and bread cubes.
Pour the vegetables and herbs over the bread. Add the eggs and stock. Stir well to blend and bake in buttered aluminum half pans at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pecan waffles
directions: Mix; pour into waffle iron and cook.
Waffles are done when steam stops rising from sides of iron.

title: hot puffy cheese balls
directions: Place water, salt, nutmeg and butter in a 2-quart saucepan. Bring mixture to a full rolling boil over high heat.
Add flour, all at once.
Remove pan from heat.
Stir until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Beat in eggs, one at a time until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Add cheese and stir until blended. Drop mixture by teaspoons into almonds in a shallow pan.
Roll to coat evenly and shape each into a 3/4-inch ball.
Place on waxed paper and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: three cheese stuffed shells
directions: Cook
shells,
drain
and cool.
Mix all cheese (except Parmesan),	eggs and seasonings in a large bowl.
Stuff cheese mixture
into shells.
Pour spaghetti sauce on bottom of two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Place stuffed shells in pan, close together. Top with
sauce
and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
Serves 6 to 12.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
In any dish, layer graham cracker crumbs, pudding, graham cracker crumbs, then chocolate icing.
Chill before serving.

title: brown sugar oaties
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto greased pans. Bake in preheated oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup and sugar in a microwave bowl and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
When you take it out, put in peanuts.
Stir and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Take out and put in the vanilla and butter.
Put back in microwave for 1 minute.
Take out and put in the soda.
Stir and pour on greased cookie sheet or pizza pan as fast as you can because it sets up fast.

title: grandmom's christmas cookies
directions: Measure into bowl the flour and butter
Cut butter into flour with fingertips.
Then add egg yolk, and sour cream.
Mix well and shape into ball.
Sprinkle with flour and knead until smooth. Chill dough for 20 minutes.
Prepare filling.

title: spinach-strawberry salad
directions: Wash spinach; drain and tear up in bite size pieces.
Wash strawberries; remove stems and cut in quarters.
Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.

title: carrot hot dish
directions: Mix in order given (layer).
Bake for 1/2 hour at 325°, uncovered.
Fresh carrots take longer.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer pork chops, onions, potatoes and cream of mushroom soup, about 3 layers in large casserole dish.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with lid or foil.

title: garlic wine pot roast(low cholesterol)
directions: Spray a cold Dutch oven with nonstick spray coating, then preheat over medium heat.
Brown roast on both sides in Dutch oven; drain any fat.
Add water, wine, onion, garlic, bouillon, thyme and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In medium bowl, stir in chopped strawberries, eggs and oil. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nuts.
Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients.
Put into loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or until cake tester inserted comes out clean.
